{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a81f5ee73ec6b1b14","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are researching how major streaming companies build their live and VOD streaming infrastructure, to help someone write company-agnostic architecture documentation. This is RESEARCH ONLY — do not write any code.\n\nResearch the following companies and their streaming infrastructure approaches. For each, find what you can about:\n- CDN strategy (build vs buy, multi-CDN)\n- Encoding/transcoding pipeline (GPU vs CPU, codec choices, per-title encoding)\n- Origin/storage architecture (S3, custom origin, edge packaging)\n- Ingest protocols (RTMP, SRT, WebRTC/WHIP)\n- Delivery protocols (HLS, DASH, LL-HLS, CMAF)\n- Backend language choices\n- Key engineering blog posts or conference talks (2024-2026)\n\nCompanies to research:\n\n1. **Netflix** — Open Connect CDN, Live Origin, AV1 adoption, Cosmos encoding pipeline\n2. **Amazon / Prime Video / Twitch** — AWS Elemental, IVS, Twitch's Go infrastructure\n3. **Apple TV+** — HTTP Live Streaming (they created HLS), FairPlay DRM, their codec/format requirements\n4. **Disney+ / Hulu / ESPN+** — BAMTech heritage, their streaming platform, live sports streaming (ESPN+)\n5. **YouTube / Google** — YouTube Live, VP9/AV1, DASH usage, infrastructure scale\n\nFor each company, note:\n- What tech decisions overlap with the project choices (CMAF, Go, Kafka, S3-compatible storage, LL-HLS, fault tolerance)\n- What differs and why\n- Any public blog posts, conference talks, or engineering documentation from 2024-2026\n\nThe goal is to write ADRs and a scaling document that says \"here's what the industry does\" rather than \"here's what Netflix does\" — making the project relevant regardless of which company the person interviews at.\n\nSearch for recent (2024-2026) engineering blog posts, conference talks, and technical documentation from these companies."},"uuid":"f32e7491-74da-43f6-81be-9ea3a70d68fe","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:15:15.805Z"}
