{"parentUuid":"13fb03cc-1c41-4a6b-b186-e87021b5a661","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a81f5ee73ec6b1b14","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0153uysWScw2pPiu6TpUBBfB","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Apple TV+ streaming infrastructure HTTP Live Streaming FairPlay DRM codec requirements 2024 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Apple FairPlay DRM: Video Protection on iOS & Safari in 2025\",\"url\":\"https://www.vdocipher.com/blog/fairplay-drm-ios-safari-html5/\"},{\"title\":\"FairPlay Streaming Overview  Developer\",\"url\":\"https://developer.apple.com/streaming/fps/FairPlayStreamingOverview.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Apple FairPlay DRM - Secure Video Streaming with DoveRunner\",\"url\":\"https://pallycon.com/apple-fairplay-drm/\"},{\"title\":\"How Does Apple’s Fairplay DRM Protect Your Videos?\",\"url\":\"https://www.muvi.com/blogs/how-apple-fairplay-drm-protects-your-video/\"},{\"title\":\"Apple FairPlay Streaming DRM - How Does It Work? - OTTVerse\",\"url\":\"https://ottverse.com/apple-fairplay-streaming-drm-how-does-it-work/\"},{\"title\":\"Apple FairPlay DRM (HLS)\",\"url\":\"https://docs.uplynk.com/docs/apple-fairplay-drm\"},{\"title\":\"The Ultimate Guide to Implementing Apple FairPlay DRM | by Shaikhhanzala | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@shaikhhanzala27/the-ultimate-guide-to-implementing-apple-fairplay-drm-4d59a0b78373\"},{\"title\":\"DRM Fairplay Setup for iOS, tvOS, Safari | Help | Uscreen\",\"url\":\"https://help.uscreen.tv/en/articles/13130532-drm-fairplay-setup-for-ios-tvos-safari\"},{\"title\":\"Apple® FairPlay Streaming DRM – Intertrust ExpressPlay\",\"url\":\"https://www.expressplay.com/products/apple-fairplay-streaming-drm/\"},{\"title\":\"Cracking the code: Apple’s DRM Technology (Part-1) | TO THE NEW Blog\",\"url\":\"https://www.tothenew.com/blog/cracking-the-code-apples-drm-technology-part-1/\"}]\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"4K HEVC h.265 Media Sharing from Mac to A… - Apple Community\",\"url\":\"https://discussions.apple.com/thread/255955109\"},{\"title\":\"Apple TV 4K - Technical Specifications - Apple\",\"url\":\"https://www.apple.com/apple-tv-4k/specs/\"},{\"title\":\"How to Stream 4K H.265/HEVC Videos to Apple TV\",\"url\":\"https://softorino.com/blog/hevc-apple-tv\"},{\"title\":\"Apple TV 4K H.265/HEVC - Play 4K H.265/HEVC on Apple TV 4K\",\"url\":\"https://www.acrok.com/play-4k-h265-hevc-on-apple-tv-4k/\"},{\"title\":\"Apple has chosen HEVC as its next-generation video codec - FlatpanelsHD\",\"url\":\"https://www.flatpanelshd.com/news.php?subaction=showfull&id=1496905696\"},{\"title\":\"Apple TV: H.265 Support - PC Outlet\",\"url\":\"https://pcoutlet.com/systems/smart-devices/apple-tv-h-265-support\"},{\"title\":\"apple support for h.265 - Apple Community\",\"url\":\"https://discussions.apple.com/thread/252582391\"},{\"title\":\"Appletv 4k home sharing app do not read 4… - Apple Community\",\"url\":\"https://discussions.apple.com/thread/255247766\"},{\"title\":\"HEVC Support - Apple Community\",\"url\":\"https://discussions.apple.com/thread/7977880\"},{\"title\":\"Does Apple TV h.265 video work with 15mbp… - Apple Community\",\"url\":\"https://discussions.apple.com/thread/251624645\"}]\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Apple CDN Infrastructure: How iCloud and Apple TV Scale Globally\",\"url\":\"https://blog.blazingcdn.com/en-us/apple-cdn-infrastructure-icloud-apple-tv-scale-globally\"},{\"title\":\"The Technology Behind Apple TV+’s Lag-Free 4K HDR Streaming\",\"url\":\"https://www.frugaltesting.com/blog/the-technology-behind-apple-tv-s-lag-free-4k-hdr-streaming\"},{\"title\":\"Apple TV - Domains, IPs and App Information\",\"url\":\"https://www.netify.ai/resources/applications/apple-tv\"},{\"title\":\"Apple's CDN is online - iTunes to benefit - FlatpanelsHD\",\"url\":\"https://www.flatpanelshd.com/news.php?subaction=showfull&id=1406878540\"},{\"title\":\"Maximizing Performance: A Comprehensive Guide to Utilizing Apple's CDN for Enhanced Content Delivery\",\"url\":\"https://locall.host/apple-cdn/\"},{\"title\":\"Apple's CDN Plans Would Give It Greater Control Over Streaming For Expanded Offerings | TechCrunch\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2014/02/04/apple-cdn-plans/\"},{\"title\":\"Building Subscription-Ready TV App Experiences: The CTO's Strategic Guide to Connected TV Architecture\",\"url\":\"https://www.nami.ml/blog/building-subscription-ready-tv-app-experiences\"},{\"title\":\"Dissecting Apple’s Meta-CDN during an iOS Update Jeremias Blendin\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/1810.02978\"},{\"title\":\"Live Streaming CDN: What Broadcaster Need to Know | Stormit\",\"url\":\"https://www.stormit.cloud/blog/live-streaming-cdn-guide/\"},{\"title\":\"CDN Infrastructure for Streaming\",\"url\":\"https://blazingcdn.com/infrastructure-for-streaming/\"}]\n\nHere's a comprehensive overview of Apple TV+'s streaming infrastructure, HTTP Live Streaming (HLS), FairPlay DRM, and codec requirements:\n\n---\n\n## Apple TV+ Streaming Infrastructure\n\n### HTTP Live Streaming (HLS)\n\nFairPlay Streaming is a DRM solution from Apple to securely deliver streaming media using the HLS (HTTP Live Streaming) protocol. Before encrypting videos, they must first be packaged using the HTTP Live Streaming (HLS) protocol. HLS is a streaming protocol from Apple used for ABR (adaptive bitrate) streaming and can support file storage in both MPEG-TS (ts) or fragmented mp4 (fmp4) container formats.\n\nAdaptive bitrate streaming formats supported by Apple FairPlay Streaming include HLS with multiplexed MPEG-TS, and Common Media Application Format (CMAF, using fMP4). FPS also supports the Common Encryption (CENC; ISO/IEC 23001-7:2016) standard.\n\n### Content Delivery Network (CDN)\n\nApple TV uses an in-house company content delivery network (CDN). The CDN delivers content to the very edge of the network and is often hosted inside Internet Service Provider (ISP) networks.\n\nThe secret behind Apple TV+'s smooth 4K HDR streaming is its global, highly optimized infrastructure. Instead of relying solely on bandwidth, Apple combines powerful CDNs, edge computing, adaptive bitrate streaming, and advanced compression to deliver cinematic-quality HDR content to millions of viewers without buffering. Apple has leveraged its position as both a hardware and software ecosystem leader to integrate these systems more tightly than most competitors.\n\nBesides using third-party CDNs, Apple has created a substantial cache infrastructure of CDN sites. Their density of sites is the highest in the USA followed by Europe and East Asia.\n\n---\n\n## FairPlay DRM\n\n### Overview\n\nFairPlay is Apple's DRM technology, which is used by Apple exclusively to stream content securely on iOS app, iOS Safari, macOS Safari as well as tvOS. FairPlay Streaming (FPS) securely delivers encrypted content through HTTP Live Streaming (HLS) and CBCS protocol.\n\nFPS securely delivers keys to Apple mobile devices, Apple TV, and Safari on OS X, which enables playback of encrypted video content. This content is delivered over the Web using HTTP Live Streaming (HLS).\n\n### Security Architecture\n\nApple devices such as macOS, iOS, watchOS, and tvOS come equipped with hardware-level security, making them highly secure environments for deploying FairPlay DRM. Unlike other DRM systems like Widevine, which can also operate on Apple devices through browsers or SDKs, FPS offers native hardware DRM support. This hardware integration is crucial for securing premium content.\n\nThe key handling and the content decryption occur on the kernel of the iOS device. In other words, the content as well as the content key are kept on the device kernel for the decryption.\n\n### Encryption\n\nAfter packaging, the content must be encrypted using AES-128 CBC encryption where CBC stands for Cipher Block Chaining. The CBC mode uses the output of the last block encryption to affect the current block.\n\nFPS allows a content provider to securely deliver an AES 128-bit content key from the provider's key server. The content provider encrypts the H.264 video content with the content key.\n\n### Key Features\n\n- **HDCP Enforcement**: FPS always enforces HDCP for each protected content block.\n- **Offline Playback**: FPS supports persistence of the security material for offline playback.\n- **AirPlay Support**: FPS supports AirPlay streaming to Apple TV.\n- **Content Key Expiration**: Starting with iOS 9, FPS allows the server to send an expiring content key to Apple mobile devices and Apple TV. Creating the time-limited key begins with the playback device sending its time reference to the server in the SPC message. The server manages the key's expiration according to the playback device's context.\n- **EME Support**: FairPlay Streaming also acts as the Content Decryption Module (CDM) of Apple's Safari web browser. The CDM enables HTML5 (native) playback of FPS protected content without any Safari plugins. FPS implements support for Encrypted Media Extensions (EME), a specification defined by the W3C for providing a communication channel between web browsers and DRM clients.\n\n---\n\n## Codec Requirements\n\n### Video Codecs\n\nFPS supports the H.264 video codec and AAC-LC, HE-AACV1-2, AC-3, and EC-3 audio codecs.\n\nFor Apple TV 4K devices, the supported video codecs are broader:\n\nThe Apple TV 4K models support 4K video with high efficiency video coding (HEVC/H.265), which provides better compression and smaller file size compared to older codecs. Supported video formats include H.264, HEVC (H.265), HEVC Dolby Vision, and MPEG-4.\n\nH.264/HEVC SDR video up to 2160p, 60 fps, Main/Main 10 profile. HEVC Dolby Vision (Profile 5)/HDR10 (Main 10 profile) up to 2160p.\n\nThe Apple TV 4K, powered by the A15 Bionic chip, decodes 4K HDR HEVC with Dolby Vision and Dolby Atmos at high bitrates without stutter.\n\n### Audio Codecs\n\nSupported audio formats include HE-AAC (V1), AAC (up to 320 Kbps), protected AAC (from iTunes Store), MP3 (up to 320 Kbps), MP3 VBR, Apple Lossless, FLAC, AIFF, and WAV; AC-3 (Dolby Digital 5.1), E-AC-3 (Dolby Digital Plus 7.1 surround sound), and Dolby Atmos.\n\nApple TV doesn't support Dolby TrueHD, nor Dolby Atmos as substream in Dolby TrueHD (like Blu-ray). Apple TV 4K does support Dolby Atmos as substream in Dolby Digital Plus (E-AC3+Atmos) for streaming.\n\n### HEVC Codec ID Requirements\n\nThere are two codec IDs in use for H.265 HEVC: hvc1 and hev1. One is compatible with Apple's decoders, the other is not. The difference between these is more than just 4 characters—it is also how the media file is structured. Apple wants the former ID (hvc1).\n\n---\n\n## Key Workflow Summary\n\nThe FairPlay DRM workflow operates as follows:\n\n1. FairPlay Streaming (FPS) secures OTT content using two main components: Encryption of HLS content (AES-128 per-frame encryption), and a key exchange process that ensures only authorized Apple devices can decrypt and play it.\n\n2. The app delegate takes care of the coordination & communication between the player, AVFoundation Framework, and the Key Server. The Key Server manages the keys used for encrypting and decrypting FairPlay-protected content.\n\n3. With FPS technology, content providers, encoding vendors, and content delivery networks (CDNs) can encrypt content, safely exchange content, and protect playback in iOS, tvOS, watchOS, and Safari browser on macOS and iOS.\n\nThis combination of HLS delivery, FairPlay DRM protection, HEVC/H.264 video codecs with Dolby Vision/HDR10 support, and Apple's own CDN infrastructure forms the backbone of how Apple TV+ delivers premium content securely to hundreds of millions of devices worldwide.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"045b88f6-8af3-4a48-9a54-dc20481065bb","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:19:26.111Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"13fb03cc-1c41-4a6b-b186-e87021b5a661"}
