{"parentUuid":"182f45f6-802f-44ef-b382-0d4e5730482d","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a81f5ee73ec6b1b14","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DHSoi6biXAPu9psSSFY4vu","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Disney+ Hulu ESPN+ BAMTech streaming platform architecture engineering 2024 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Disney+ - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disney+\"},{\"title\":\"How Media Engineers Enable Disney’s Streaming Connection with Audiences - Life at Disney\",\"url\":\"https://sites.disney.com/lifeatdisney/work-and-innovation/2024/08/02/how-media-engineers-enable-disneys-streaming-connection-with-audiences/\"},{\"title\":\"Disney Streaming - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disney_Streaming\"},{\"title\":\"From BAMTech to the bundle: The story of Disney’s digital remastering - SportsPro\",\"url\":\"https://www.sportspromedia.com/from-the-magazine/disney-plus-espn-bamtech-fox-takeover-hulu-ott-streaming/\"},{\"title\":\"Disney+ Hulu Merger 2026: What Subscribers Need to Know | AMW®\",\"url\":\"https://amworldgroup.com/blog/disney-and-hulu-combined-app\"},{\"title\":\"Disney's ~$4B Acquisition That (Probably) Saved The Company\",\"url\":\"https://www.readtrung.com/p/disneys-4b-acquisition-that-probably\"},{\"title\":\"Bob Iger On Disney's Hulu Roll-Up And Streaming Mission: \\\"We're Prepared To Pivot In A New Direction\\\"\",\"url\":\"https://deadline.com/2019/05/bob-iger-disney-hulu-roll-up-and-streaming-mission-were-prepared-to-pivot-1202614597/\"},{\"title\":\"BAMTech Becomes Disney Streaming After a Buyout | DesignRush\",\"url\":\"https://news.designrush.com/bamtech-disney-streaming-media-takeover\"},{\"title\":\"ESPN+ - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ESPN+\"},{\"title\":\"Disney’s Hulu Takeover Sets Stage for Deeper ESPN Integration\",\"url\":\"https://frontofficesports.com/disneys-hulu-takeover-sets-stage-for-deeper-espn-integration/\"}]\n\nHere's a comprehensive overview of what I found regarding Disney+, Hulu, ESPN+, BAMTech, and their streaming platform architecture and engineering developments in 2024–2025:\n\n---\n\n## Disney Streaming Platform Architecture & Engineering (2024–2025)\n\n### The BAMTech Foundation\n\nDisney Streaming (formerly known as BAMTech Media from 2015 to 2018, and Disney Streaming Services from 2018 to 2021) is a technology subsidiary of the Walt Disney Company located in Manhattan, New York City. It was established in 2015 as a spin-off of MLB Advanced Media—the digital media arm of Major League Baseball, focused on providing video on demand technology, particularly for over-the-top (OTT) media services.\n\nBAMTech, a streaming technology services group that underpins Disney+, Hulu, and ESPN+ direct-to-consumer services, used to belong to Major League Baseball (MLB). Major League Baseball started streaming live video online with its MLB.TV in 2002 — three years before YouTube was a thing.\n\nDisney+ relies on technology developed by Disney Streaming, which was originally established as BAMTech.\n\n### Disney's Acquisition of BAMTech\n\nIn August 2016, Disney acquired a minority stake in BAMTech for $1 billion, with an option to acquire a majority stake in the future. On August 8, 2017, Disney announced that it would increase its ownership in the company to a 75% controlling stake for $1.58 billion. Disney had acquired sole ownership by November 2022.\n\nBob Iger praised BAMTech's capabilities, with SportsPro reporting him saying: \"the quality of that technology has just blown us away.\"\n\n### Media Engineering Pipeline\n\nMedia Engineering manages the content platform pipeline for all the content that flows through Disney's direct-to-consumer platforms, like Disney+, Hulu, and ESPN+. As part of this pipeline, they ingest content, metadata, and artwork, which is used to drive browsing and playback experiences.\n\nAt Disney, Media Engineering is considered essential because the technology enables a better experience for viewers around the globe. They've done \"tremendous amounts of research on what it means to properly deliver content to applications, both in the home and in mobile devices.\"\n\n### Platform Convergence: 2024–2025 Milestones\n\n1. **ESPN Hub Integration (Late 2024):** In November 2024, it was announced that an ESPN hub would be added to Disney+ in the United States on December 4; the ESPN hub would include sports broadcasts and original series available to Disney+ and Hulu subscribers, as well as integrate content from ESPN+ for users subscribed to that service.\n\n2. **ESPN+ Folded into ESPN DTC (August 2025):** ESPN+ became part of the new ESPN direct-to-consumer streaming service when it launched on August 21, 2025, with the previous ESPN+ streaming product rebranded as ESPN Select.\n\n3. **Hulu-Disney+ Unified App (2026):** Disney CEO Bob Iger announced during an earnings call that the company will combine both streaming services by 2026, creating what he described as \"an impressive package of entertainment\" featuring premium brands, general entertainment, kids' programming, news, and live sports content. In August 2025, Disney announced plans to fully merge Hulu into an updated version of the Disney+ platform in 2026, although the two services will remain separate subscriptions.\n\n4. **International Rebranding:** It was announced that Hulu would replace Star as its general entertainment brand for international markets; the rebranding took effect on October 8, 2025, accompanied by an update to the Disney+ user interface with a focus on recommendations and more visual content.\n\n### Streaming Financial Performance\n\nIn fiscal Q3 of 2024, Disney's streaming unit reported its first operating profit ($47m) followed by a larger gain in fiscal Q4 2024 ($321m). This was after the unit lost $4B in 2022.\n\nIn the third quarter of 2024, the number of global Disney+ subscribers amounted to 153.8 million, marking a growth of around seven million compared with the same quarter of the previous year.\n\n### The Strategic Significance of BAMTech\n\nWhen Disney made an all-in bet on streaming to take on Netflix, it had to buy the little-known technology unit incubated within the MLB called BAMTech. Disney had a fork-in-the-road decision and was able to execute quickly on the streaming path because of BAMTech.\n\nWith the acquisition of BAMTech, Disney began to develop two subscription streaming services aligned with Disney properties: the sports-oriented ESPN+ and the global family entertainment service Disney+; U.S. general entertainment service Hulu and Latin America's Star+ were later transferred into the company in August 2021.\n\n---\n\nIn summary, the BAMTech acquisition provided the critical technical backbone for Disney's entire streaming ecosystem. Through 2024 and 2025, Disney has been aggressively converging its three platforms (Disney+, Hulu, and ESPN+) into a unified streaming architecture, with a fully merged app expected in 2026.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"39c32798-ca7e-4aa7-92fc-7aba85926dbd","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:20:05.887Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"182f45f6-802f-44ef-b382-0d4e5730482d"}
