{"parentUuid":"9f440cf9-9f6a-492b-ac55-3b89e61230dd","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a81f5ee73ec6b1b14","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"query_update","query":"Disney streaming BAMTech backend programming language Java Scala microservices live sports"},"toolUseID":"search-progress-1","parentToolUseID":"toolu_014XVrqtgVaxayc5oA5kFLT7","uuid":"2d378efd-32f9-419e-8c5e-b18bc2c51876","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:25:45.601Z"}
{"parentUuid":"2d378efd-32f9-419e-8c5e-b18bc2c51876","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a81f5ee73ec6b1b14","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"search_results_received","resultCount":10,"query":"Disney streaming BAMTech backend programming language Java Scala microservices live sports"},"toolUseID":"srvtoolu_01EUqLYz7YAstqty7iEs2buR","parentToolUseID":"toolu_014XVrqtgVaxayc5oA5kFLT7","uuid":"3f7a0d13-d7f8-47fb-a652-572db0d06d74","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:25:47.868Z"}
{"parentUuid":"9c2f0ba5-bd33-4df7-8884-113aa49a02d6","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a81f5ee73ec6b1b14","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014XVrqtgVaxayc5oA5kFLT7","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Disney streaming BAMTech backend programming language Java Scala microservices live sports\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Which Programming Languages Are Being Used by Popular Streaming Services (Netflix, Apple TV, Amazon Prime, YouTube…)? - DEV Community\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/emma_richardson/which-programming-languages-are-being-used-by-popular-streaming-services-netflix-apple-tv-amazon-41n1\"},{\"title\":\"Top Programming Languages Used Behind Disney Hotstar Streaming Service\",\"url\":\"https://www.technologywithvivek.com/2024/07/Top%20Programming%20Languages%20Used%20in%20Disney%20Hotstar%20Streaming%20Service.html\"},{\"title\":\"DISNEY STREAMING SERVICES (BAMTECH Media) | Senior Software Engineers | Full Tim... | Hacker News\",\"url\":\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=17663135\"},{\"title\":\"Disney Streaming - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disney_Streaming\"},{\"title\":\"BAMTECH Media | Disney Wiki | Fandom\",\"url\":\"https://disney.fandom.com/wiki/BAMTECH_Media\"},{\"title\":\"Disney Streaming · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/disneystreaming\"},{\"title\":\"Senior Software Engineer at 5014 Disney Streaming Technology LLC - Jobs 4 Student Athletes\",\"url\":\"https://www.jobs4studentathletes.com/jobs/187168945-senior-software-engineer\"},{\"title\":\"The Engine Behind Disney + Hotstar: A Peek into Their Backend Infrastructure - GeeksforGeeks\",\"url\":\"https://geeksforgeeks.org/the-engine-behind-disney-hotstar-a-peek-into-their-backend-infrastructure\"},{\"title\":\"Sr. Software Engineer (Scala) job in New York at Disney | Lensa\",\"url\":\"https://lensa.com/sr-software-engineer-scala-jobs/new-york/jd/d94641fe3ced12753b6fa9cd6adbf844\"},{\"title\":\"How to Build a Scalable Livestream Application in Java\",\"url\":\"https://www.fastpix.io/blog/how-to-build-livestream-application-in-java\"}]\n\nHere's a summary of what I found regarding Disney Streaming (BAMTech) and their backend technology stack:\n\n## Disney Streaming / BAMTech: Backend Technology Overview\n\n### Company Background\nDisney Streaming (formerly known as BAMTech Media from 2015 to 2018, and Disney Streaming Services from 2018 to 2021) is a technology subsidiary of the Walt Disney Company located in Manhattan, New York City. It was established in 2015 as a spin-off of MLB Advanced Media—the digital media arm of Major League Baseball, focused on providing video on demand technology, particularly for over-the-top (OTT) media services.\n\nThe company's major clients include ESPN (for its ESPN, ESPN+ and ESPN3 services), the National Hockey League, and Blaze Media.\n\n### Products and Services\nBAMTECH Media develops premium digital media products for many of its partners such as MLB.TV, NHL.TV, PlayStation Vue, and ESPN+. They are paving the way for next-generation media and sports technologies. Media Engineering works on building out scalable distributed systems for media production pipeline that is core to their products.\n\n### Programming Languages: Java, Scala, and More\nDisney+ uses Java, Python, and Go as its primary backend languages.\n\nFor the Disney Streaming / BAMTech Audience Data and Measurement team specifically, as a Senior Software Engineer, candidates are expected to use \"deep Java, Scala, Python, scripting, DevOps, and data persistence skills to write and test code that delivers new features.\"\n\nThis is a dynamic, cross-domain team delivering end-to-end solutions across diverse technical areas, including machine learning, big data, microservices, and data visualization.\n\n### Big Data & Microservices Stack\nDisney Streaming requires 5+ years of experience in big data application development using Java, Scala, and Python, including familiarity with modern frameworks and platforms such as Spark, Flink, Singlestore, Kafka, Nifi, and AWS big data technologies.\n\n### Scala at Disney Streaming\nOn November 7, 2017, BAMTech acquired the Manchester-based software firm Cake Solutions — a company well-known for its Scala expertise, further underscoring BAMTech's investment in Scala-based technologies. Disney Streaming also has 21 repositories available on GitHub, many of which feature Scala-based open-source projects.\n\n### Disney+ Hotstar (Live Sports)\nJava is renowned for its stability and scalability, making it an ideal choice for Hotstar's backend services. With robust libraries and frameworks like Spring, Java enables the development of secure, high-performance, and maintainable applications. Hotstar leverages Java for handling user authentication, transaction management, and other critical backend services.\n\nScala, running on the Java Virtual Machine (JVM), is used by Hotstar for its data processing needs. With its ability to handle large-scale data with Apache Spark, Scala is ideal for processing and analyzing the vast amounts of user data generated daily. Scala's functional programming features and compatibility with Java make it a powerful tool for data-intensive applications.\n\nHotstar employs Go for its microservices architecture, ensuring that services can handle high traffic without compromising speed.\n\n### Live Sports Scalability\nOn 15 November 2023, when India was playing against New Zealand at the World Cup semifinal match, more than 5 crore people were watching the match on the Disney+ Hotstar OTT apps on a global level. The infrastructure is designed for scalability, ensuring that millions of users can access live streaming simultaneously without compromising performance.\n\nIn summary, Disney Streaming (BAMTech) relies heavily on **Java** and **Scala** (both JVM languages) along with **Python** and **Go** for its backend and microservices architecture. Scala plays a particularly important role in data processing and big data pipelines, while Java powers core backend services. The microservices approach, combined with technologies like Kafka, Spark, and Flink, enables the platform to handle massive concurrent loads during live sports events.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"b2755713-7a18-4f8d-84df-7cebc24940af","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:26:14.114Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"9c2f0ba5-bd33-4df7-8884-113aa49a02d6"}
