{"parentUuid":"a125c2c3-e2de-41b8-b25e-00f2f805bf21","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a81f5ee73ec6b1b14","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BnQtk52eyRt4iH1GsT5vb7","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Apple HLS authoring specification codec requirements 2024 2025 AV1 HEVC\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"HTTP Live Streaming (HLS) Authoring Specification for Apple devices appendixes | Apple Developer Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/http-live-streaming/hls-authoring-specification-for-apple-devices-appendixes\"},{\"title\":\"HLS Authoring Update - WWDC17 - Videos - Apple Developer\",\"url\":\"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2017/515/\"},{\"title\":\"HTTP Live Streaming (HLS) authoring specification for Apple devices | Apple Developer Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/http-live-streaming/hls-authoring-specification-for-apple-devices\"},{\"title\":\"An update to Apple HLS best practices (end 2024) - Radiant Media Player\",\"url\":\"https://www.radiantmediaplayer.com/blog/an-update-to-apple-hls-best-practices-end-2024.html\"},{\"title\":\"What's new in HTTP Live Streaming WWDC 2025 June 2025\",\"url\":\"https://developer.apple.com/streaming/Whats-new-HLS.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Apple Got It Wrong: Encoding Specs for HEVC in HLS\",\"url\":\"https://www.streamingmedia.com/Articles/ReadArticle.aspx?ArticleID=121878\"},{\"title\":\"Authoring 4K and HDR HLS Streams - Tech Talks - Videos - Apple Developer\",\"url\":\"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks/501/\"},{\"title\":\"Apple Updates HLS Authoring Spec for 4K and HDR - Streaming Learning Center\",\"url\":\"https://streaminglearningcenter.com/blogs/apple-updates-hls-authoring-spec-4k-hdr.html\"},{\"title\":\"HLS updates from WWDC 2024\",\"url\":\"https://bitmovin.com/blog/hls-updates-wwdc-2024/\"},{\"title\":\"HEVC in HLS: 10 Key Questions for Streaming Video Developers - Streaming Learning Center\",\"url\":\"https://streaminglearningcenter.com/codecs/hevc-hls-10-key-questions-streaming-video-developers.html\"}]\n\nHere's a summary of what the search results reveal about Apple's HLS Authoring Specification codec requirements, including information relevant to 2024–2025 and AV1/HEVC support:\n\n---\n\n## Apple HLS Authoring Specification: Codec Requirements (2024–2025)\n\n### Supported Video Codecs\n\nAll video MUST be encoded using H.264/AVC, HEVC/H.265, Dolby Vision, or AV1. This confirms that as of late 2024, Apple's HLS specification officially supports four video codecs.\n\n### AV1 Support (New in 2024)\n\nWith Apple adding AV1 decoders in their latest generation of processors, they've defined how to signal that content within HLS playlists.\n\nApple has also introduced **Dolby Vision with AV1** support in HLS:\n- They are using Dolby Vision Profile 10, which is Dolby's 10-bit AV1 aware profile. HLS will now support 3 different Dolby Vision profiles: 10, 10.1 and 10.4. Profile 10 is \"true\" Dolby Vision, 10.1 is their backward compatible version of HDR10, and 10.4 their backward compatible version of Hybrid Log Gamma (HLG).\n- For profiles 10.1 and 10.4, you need to use a SUPPLEMENTAL-CODECS brand attribute and the correct VIDEO-RANGE. For these, 10.1 should use 'db1p' and PQ, and 10.4 should use 'db4h' and HLG. The full example codec string they provided is: CODECS=\"av01.0.13M.10.0.112″, SUPPLEMENTAL-CODECS=\"dav1.10.09/db4h\", VIDEO-RANGE=HLG.\n\n### HEVC Requirements\n\n- Profile, Level, and Tier for HEVC MUST be less than or equal to Main10 Profile, Level 5.0, High Tier.\n- Like H.264, HEVC has different profiles, two of which are available for HLS—Main and Main 10. Main10 encodes in either 8-bit or 10-bit bit depths, while Main is 8-bit only. HLS can handle either, though you'll need to produce in Main 10 format for HDR output.\n- The container format for HEVC video MUST be fMP4 (fragmented MP4 files).\n- The addition of support for HEVC enables the delivery of higher quality video at about a 40 percent lower bit rate compared to H.264. HDR video must be delivered using HEVC. There are two HDR formats that we support: Dolby Vision and HDR10.\n\n### HDR Requirements\n\n- High Dynamic Range (HDR) HEVC video MUST be HDR10 or DolbyVision.\n- For HDR content, frame rates less than or equal to 30 fps SHOULD be provided.\n- For backward compatibility, SDR streams MUST be provided.\n\n### Backward Compatibility Best Practices\n\n- Always use the CODECS attribute. You need this so that older players don't try to play the HEVC content. Second and almost as important, always include some H.264 content. You need this so older players will have something that they can play.\n\n### General Segmentation & Frame Rate Guidelines\n\n- Target durations SHOULD be 6 seconds (for fMP4 HLS or MPEG TS HLS). Video segments MUST start with an IDR frame.\n- Video on Demand (VOD) content SHOULD use a natural frame rate for the content. Frame rates 23.976, 24, 25, 29.97, 30, 50, 59.94, and 60 fps are supported.\n- The HLS Authoring Specification prohibits frame rates beyond 60 fps for all codecs.\n\n### WWDC 2025 Updates\n\nApple provides authoring guidelines related to spatial videos in the HLS authoring specification for Apple devices. The 2025 updates include features like MediaFileSegmenter now supporting segmenting PFRM (Per Frame Rectangular Mask) content and a new characteristic \"public.machine-generated\" to indicate a rendition that's authored with machine-generated content, plus a new preload schema for HLS date range resources.\n\n---\n\n### Key Resources\n\n- **Official Spec**: [HLS Authoring Specification for Apple Devices](https://developer.apple.com/documentation/http-live-streaming/hls-authoring-specification-for-apple-devices)\n- **What's New in HLS (WWDC 2025)**: [Apple PDF](https://developer.apple.com/streaming/Whats-new-HLS.pdf)\n- **Appendixes**: [HLS Authoring Spec Appendixes](https://developer.apple.com/documentation/http-live-streaming/hls-authoring-specification-for-apple-devices-appendixes)\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"fddd4daf-56aa-4591-afb9-2fd95e9d8372","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:29:14.913Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a125c2c3-e2de-41b8-b25e-00f2f805bf21"}
