{"parentUuid":"ae852db9-e581-4f3d-8a6e-dd86a23c7865","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CWKp9oYVoEY3894cPa9SR2","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Warner Bros Discovery streaming CDN provider Akamai multi-CDN strategy\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Global CDN Services Market About $5B in 2023, Expected To Grow 3% In 2024, Driven by AWS\",\"url\":\"https://www.streamingmediablog.com/2024/07/cdn-market-size.html\"},{\"title\":\"Akamai CDN — Content Delivery Network Solutions | Akamai\",\"url\":\"https://www.akamai.com/solutions/content-delivery-network\"},{\"title\":\"Inside Disney+ Streaming Technology: Transcoding, ABR, And Akamai CDN Explained\",\"url\":\"https://www.frugaltesting.com/blog/inside-disney-streaming-technology-transcoding-abr-and-akamai-cdn-explained\"},{\"title\":\"What Are Streaming Media Services? | Akamai\",\"url\":\"https://www.akamai.com/glossary/what-are-streaming-media-services\"},{\"title\":\"Stop Losing Viewers: 10 Best Video CDN Providers for Live Streaming in 2025\",\"url\":\"https://blog.blazingcdn.com/en-us/the-10-best-video-cdn-providers-for-live-streaming-2024\"},{\"title\":\"Live Streaming CDN: What Broadcaster Need to Know | Stormit\",\"url\":\"https://www.stormit.cloud/blog/live-streaming-cdn-guide/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery CTO and CPO explain how they made Max less buggy | TechCrunch\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2023/05/05/warner-bros-discovery-cto-and-cpo-explain-how-they-made-max-less-buggy/\"},{\"title\":\"Akamai gives more visibility into CDN purchases - CSI Magazine\",\"url\":\"https://csimagazine.com/csi/Akamai-gives-more-visibility-into-CDN-purchases.php\"},{\"title\":\"Best 3 multi-CDN providers in 2025\",\"url\":\"https://www.cloudcomputing-news.net/news/best-3-multi-cdn-providers-in-2025/\"},{\"title\":\"CDN & Multi CDN Strategies - Criticalcase\",\"url\":\"https://www.criticalcase.com/cdn-multi-cdn-strategies\"}]\n\nHere are the findings on Warner Bros. Discovery's streaming CDN strategy, including their use of Akamai and a multi-CDN approach:\n\n## Warner Bros. Discovery's Multi-CDN Streaming Strategy\n\n### Multi-CDN Approach for Max\n\nTo achieve faster performance and more stability, Warner Bros. Discovery CTO Avi Saxena confirmed that Max uses multiple CDNs (content delivery networks) to give the app improved resiliency. \"So when something goes down, the product still continues to work,\" he explained. Max uses four CDNs — **Amazon CloudFront**, **Google's Cloud CDN**, **Akamai**, and **Fastly**.\n\n### Scale of Content Delivery\n\nMax also uses AWS as a primary cloud provider, which millions of companies rely on for storage, databases, and cloud-compute. \"In any given month, we deliver more than an exabyte worth of content, which is 1,000 petabytes a month, which is a big amount. And you cannot rely on just one CDN to do that,\" Saxena added.\n\n### Background: Building the Max Platform\n\nBefore Warner Bros. Discovery launched its new HBO Max/Discovery+ streaming service (Max), WBD's CTO and CPO focused on building the new platform from the ground up, improving functionality, and ensuring a smooth viewing experience. Merging two streaming services together was a complex challenge, and overall, the company underwent 12 months of planning to build a cohesive platform that serves all types of customers.\n\n### Akamai's Role in the Broader Streaming Industry\n\nAs one of the founding giants of CDN technology, Akamai continues to lead the way in secure, reliable, and highly distributed content delivery, serving Fortune 500 companies, financial institutions, and the world's largest media companies. Akamai is more than just a CDN — it's an edge computing and security platform capable of handling traffic delivery, app acceleration, API protection, bot management, and Zero Trust security.\n\n### Why Multi-CDN Is the Industry Standard\n\nWarner Bros. Discovery's approach mirrors a broader trend among major streaming services. Relying on one vendor is considered outdated; blending, for example, Akamai's sheer edge density with other CDN providers can fortify resilience while lowering cost per terabyte. A multi-CDN strategy helps reduce latency and costs, improving performance by routing real-time traffic to the CDN provider that delivers the best cost/performance ratio.\n\nIn summary, Warner Bros. Discovery employs a robust **four-CDN strategy** (Akamai, Amazon CloudFront, Google Cloud CDN, and Fastly) for its Max streaming platform, delivering over an exabyte of content per month. Akamai is one of the key CDN partners, but the multi-CDN approach ensures redundancy, resilience, and cost optimization at massive scale.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"e79d6bea-6d11-42af-afb4-4e87e0e23d84","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:39:26.721Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ae852db9-e581-4f3d-8a6e-dd86a23c7865"}
