{"parentUuid":"eb6b69b7-07e1-4f9d-88f3-de4cbceb7ffb","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018BxyGMPWnSNeQsCD6WPKKk","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Warner Bros Discovery Max encoding pipeline codec H.264 HEVC AV1 per-title encoding\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Per‑Title Before New Codecs: Fixing Your H.264 Baseline - Streaming Learning Center\",\"url\":\"https://streaminglearningcenter.com/codecs/per-title-before-new-codecs.html\"},{\"title\":\"HEVC vs. H.264: Bandwidth and Cost Savings\",\"url\":\"https://www.streamingmedia.com/Articles/ReadArticle.aspx?ArticleID=161357\"},{\"title\":\"Understanding Video Codecs: H.264, H.265 (HEVC), VP9 & AV1 Compared\",\"url\":\"https://pixflow.net/blog/understanding-video-codecs-h-264-hevc-h-265-vp9-and-av1-explained/\"},{\"title\":\"H.265 Codec Explained: High Efficiency Video Coding (HEVC) Guide\",\"url\":\"https://antmedia.io/h265-hevc-codec-explained/\"},{\"title\":\"HEVC vs. H.264: Bandwidth and Cost Savings - Streaming Media Producer\",\"url\":\"https://www.streamingmedia.com/Producer/Articles/Editorial/Featured-Articles/HEVC-vs.-H.264-Bandwidth-and-Cost-Savings-161358.aspx\"},{\"title\":\"AV1 vs. H.264: Which Codec Should You Use?\",\"url\":\"https://getstream.io/blog/av1-h264/\"},{\"title\":\"Download Handout – Comparison of H.264, HEVC, VP9 and AV1 - Streaming Learning Center\",\"url\":\"https://streaminglearningcenter.com/codecs/download-handout-comparison-h-264-hevc-vp9-av1.html\"},{\"title\":\"AV1 or HEVC?: How to Choose the Right Video Codec | Dolby OptiView\",\"url\":\"https://optiview.dolby.com/resources/blog/playback/av1-or-hevc-how-to-choose-the-right-video-codec/\"},{\"title\":\"Decoding the Video Codec Wars: H.264, HEVC, and AV1 Compared for Streaming\",\"url\":\"https://flussonic.com/blog/news/evolution-of-video-codecs\"},{\"title\":\"AV1 vs HEVC: Video Codec Guide 2024 - Video Tap\",\"url\":\"https://videotap.com/blog/av1-vs-hevc-video-codec-guide-2024\"}]\n\nThe search results didn't return specific information about Warner Bros. Discovery's Max streaming service encoding pipeline. Let me do a more targeted search.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"WarnerBros.com | Warner Bros. Discovery Unveils Max Streaming Service | Press Releases\",\"url\":\"https://www.warnerbros.com/news/press-releases/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-max-streaming-service\"},{\"title\":\"Max: the Warner Bros. Discovery streaming service explained | Stuff\",\"url\":\"https://www.stuff.tv/features/max-the-new-warner-bros-discovery-streaming-service-explained/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery reinvents linear television advertising with AWS | Amazon Web Services\",\"url\":\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/media/warner-bros-discovery-reinvents-linear-television-advertising-with-aws/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery marks Q2 streaming gains, focuses content licensing in-house\",\"url\":\"https://www.streamtvinsider.com/content/warner-bros-discovery-marks-q2-streaming-gains-focuses-content-licensing-house\"},{\"title\":\"Contact Andrew Styons, Email: d***@wbd.com & Phone Number | Encoding Specialist at Warner Bros. Discovery - ZoomInfo\",\"url\":\"https://www.zoominfo.com/p/Andrew-Styons/5331787969\"},{\"title\":\"WARNER BROS. DISCOVERY UNVEILS MAX STREAMING SERVICE\",\"url\":\"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-max-streaming-service-301795959.html\"},{\"title\":\"Welcome - Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://www.wbd.com/\"},{\"title\":\"Contact Sheriee Davis, Email: s***@wbd.com & Phone Number | Encoding Specialist at Warner Bros. Discovery - ZoomInfo\",\"url\":\"https://www.zoominfo.com/p/Sheriee-Davis/1965134871\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warner_Bros._Discovery\"},{\"title\":\"Content Partner Hub | Standard Dynamic Range (SDR)\",\"url\":\"https://partnerhub.warnermediagroup.com/specifications-and-guides/licensed/licensed-content-sdr\"}]\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"HBO Max - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HBO_Max\"},{\"title\":\"The State of AV1 Playback Support [2024 Update]\",\"url\":\"https://bitmovin.com/blog/av1-playback-support/\"},{\"title\":\"AV1 - What is it and how does it work?\",\"url\":\"https://getstream.io/glossary/av1/\"},{\"title\":\"HBO Max - Audiovisual Identity Database\",\"url\":\"https://www.avid.wiki/HBO_Max\"},{\"title\":\"H.265 Codec Explained: High Efficiency Video Coding (HEVC) Guide\",\"url\":\"https://antmedia.io/h265-hevc-codec-explained/\"},{\"title\":\"Different Video Encoding Formats and Trade-Offs - Cardinal Peak\",\"url\":\"https://www.cardinalpeak.com/blog/streaming-media-video-encoding-formats-and-trade-offs\"},{\"title\":\"HBO Max | Warner Bros. Entertainment Wiki | Fandom\",\"url\":\"https://warnerbros.fandom.com/wiki/HBO_Max\"},{\"title\":\"A/V Specs\",\"url\":\"https://brand.hbomax.com/av-specs\"},{\"title\":\"H.265 Video Codec - The Ultimate Guide to HEVC Encoding\",\"url\":\"https://www.dacast.com/blog/hevc-video-codec/\"},{\"title\":\"HBO Max | If you have the HBO Max Premium plan, you can stream select HBO Max content in 4K UHD.\",\"url\":\"https://help.hbomax.com/US/Answer/Detail/000002523\"}]\n\nLet me do one more targeted search to find the specific Streaming Media article about Warner Bros. Discovery's HEVC experience and encoding pipeline details.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"HEVC vs. H.264: Bandwidth and Cost Savings - Streaming Media Producer\",\"url\":\"https://www.streamingmedia.com/Producer/Articles/Editorial/Featured-Articles/HEVC-vs.-H.264-Bandwidth-and-Cost-Savings-161358.aspx\"},{\"title\":\"HEVC vs. H.264: Bandwidth and Cost Savings\",\"url\":\"https://www.streamingmedia.com/Articles/ReadArticle.aspx?ArticleID=161357\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warner_Bros._Discovery\"},{\"title\":\"Real-World Bandwidth Savings from VP9, HEVC, and AV1 - Streaming Learning Center\",\"url\":\"https://streaminglearningcenter.com/codecs/bandwidth-savings-vp9-hevc-av1.html\"},{\"title\":\"HEVC: What it Is, What You Need to Know\",\"url\":\"https://www.streamingmedia.com/Articles/Editorial/Featured-Articles/HEVC-What-it-Is-What-You-Need-to-Know-138059.aspx\"},{\"title\":\"Welcome - Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://www.wbd.com/\"},{\"title\":\"How Warner Bros. Discovery Is Maxing Out on Streaming\",\"url\":\"https://www.streamingmedia.com/Articles/ReadArticle.aspx?ArticleID=158852\"},{\"title\":\"The Future of Streaming and Storytelling With Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://www.adweek.com/brand-marketing/the-future-of-streaming-and-storytelling-with-warner-bros-discovery/\"},{\"title\":\"HBO Max - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HBO_Max\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery’s streaming business set to become profitable in 2023 | TechCrunch\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2023/05/05/warner-bros-discoverys-streaming-business-set-to-become-profitable-in-2023/\"}]\n\nBased on my research across multiple searches, here is what I found regarding Warner Bros. Discovery's Max encoding pipeline and codec usage:\n\n## Warner Bros. Discovery Max — Encoding Pipeline & Codec Information\n\n### HEVC Adoption and Experience\n\nThe most relevant information comes from a Streaming Media article featuring insights from Alex Zambelli (a compressionist who has worked with WBD's platform). Key findings:\n\n- The case for moving from H.264 to newer codecs like AV1 or HEVC is typically expressed in terms of encoding efficiency translating to bandwidth and cost savings. For major content companies like Warner Bros. Discovery that have adopted H.265, the question is how much their experience has borne out that hypothesis.\n\n- The increased compute costs associated with HEVC encoding diminish to some extent the benefits of migrating to the newer codec, although the shift to cloud computing and improved encoders are helping to level the playing field. \"There are certainly higher compute costs for HEVC,\" Zambelli says, \"though I think the encoders have gotten a lot better over the last several years. And most cloud computing platforms have improved in terms of their CPU offerings, so we have highly multi-threaded CPUs available in the cloud. Most encoding these days is parallelized as well.\"\n\n- Zambelli noted, \"we're definitely reaching a point where I think HEVC encoding is going to become cheap enough that it'll almost seem like a free add-on.\"\n\n- Regarding device support, \"all of our devices support AVC, and so obviously that's going to be highly cached. Over 75% of the devices support HEVC, and so we're getting a lot of caching efficiency for HEVC as well.\"\n\n- Real-world CDN savings are less than theoretical bitrate savings: reducing a 1080p encode from 6 Mbps in AVC to 4.5 Mbps in HEVC doesn't help users on 3 Mbps connections. \"Real CDN savings end up being probably closer to 5 or 10% if you're saving 20% on bitrate overall.\"\n\n### VOD Transcoding Infrastructure\n\n- AWS Elemental MediaConvert has been an important component of the WBD VOD transcoding pipeline since 2021. Then, the company began using AWS Elemental MediaLive for encoding live content.\n\n### Content Delivery Codecs\n\n- HBO Max delivers HEVC for 4K content where supported, while YouTube allows HEVC uploads but playback defaults to VP9 or AV1 unless devices explicitly support HEVC decoding.\n\n- Disney+, Hulu, and HBO Max are reported to be evaluating AV1 for future expansion.\n\n### Per-Title Encoding (Industry Context)\n\nWhile no specific details about WBD's per-title encoding implementation were found, the broader industry context is informative:\n\n- Industry experts argue: \"If you recommend that your service deploy HEVC or AV1 before implementing some form of per-title, you're committing transcoding malpractice.\"\n\n- Netflix published a report showing that in early 2022, 21% of their streamed content benefited from the most recent improvements in codec efficiency, like Per-Title optimized AV1 and HEVC. They estimated that without those improvements, total Netflix traffic globally would have been around 24% higher.\n\n### 4K/HDR Delivery on Max\n\n- The Ultimate Ad-Free tier of Max offers an expanded catalog of content available in 4K UHD including key programming such as Game of Thrones, The Last of Us, Harry Potter, Lord of the Rings, The Dark Knight Trilogy and more. All Warner Bros. movies released in 2023 and going forward are also available in 4K UHD when they arrive on Max following their theatrical windows.\n\n### Summary\n\nWarner Bros. Discovery uses a **dual-codec approach** with **H.264 (AVC) as the universal baseline** and **HEVC (H.265) for supported devices** (over 75% of their device base). Their VOD transcoding pipeline runs on **AWS Elemental MediaConvert**, and they are reportedly **evaluating AV1** for future use. No specific public details about their per-title encoding methodology were found in the search results, though the industry consensus is that per-title optimization is essential before adopting advanced codecs.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"6fec92e5-b2d0-4d9a-8527-8ea8a89a35eb","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:40:11.073Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"eb6b69b7-07e1-4f9d-88f3-de4cbceb7ffb"}
