{"parentUuid":"4bac6d95-3809-48c3-9f1e-eb9c9e955502","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VFE26CD4c6SpEA63eCbuJp","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Warner Bros Discovery Max tech stack engineering blog backend Java Go microservices\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Keeping the stories flowing at Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://thefrugalarchitect.com/architects/tom-leaman-warner-bros-discovery.html\"},{\"title\":\"Warner | Salaries, Interviews, Culture and Reviews | Fishbowl\",\"url\":\"https://www.fishbowlapp.com/company/warner\"},{\"title\":\"Staff Software Engineer - Fullstack developer (Backend) (MSC team),Bangalore at Warner Bros. Games in Bengaluru, Karnataka, India | 9-13 Years Experience\",\"url\":\"https://outscal.com/job/staff-software-engineer-fullstack-developer-backend-msc-team-bangalore-at-warner-bros-games-in-bengaluru-karnataka-india-1\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros Discovery Senior Staff Software Engineer | Welcome to the Jungle (formerly Otta)\",\"url\":\"https://app.welcometothejungle.com/jobs/dSn-cO2c\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Sports implements further live cloud-based production using AWS | AWS for M&E Blog\",\"url\":\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/media/warner-bros-discovery-sports-implements-further-live-cloud-based-production-using-aws/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery plans migration to a single tech stack | CIO Dive\",\"url\":\"https://www.ciodive.com/news/warner-bros-discovery-plus-technology-merger/629012/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery - Software Engineer - Java Full Stack Development | hirist.tech\",\"url\":\"https://www.hirist.tech/j/warner-bros-discovery-software-engineer-java-full-stack-development-1534711\"},{\"title\":\"Varun Chopra - Senior Web Application Engineer at Warner Bros. Discovery | The Org\",\"url\":\"https://theorg.com/org/warner-bros-discovery/org-chart/varun-chopra\"},{\"title\":\"What tech stack is commonly used for microservices? | Alex Xu posted on the topic | LinkedIn\",\"url\":\"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/alexxubyte_systemdesign-coding-interviewtips-activity-7111733744280948737-EbxW\"},{\"title\":\"Top 5 Technologies to Build Microservices Architecture\",\"url\":\"https://www.sayonetech.com/blog/best-technologies-build-microservices-architecture/\"}]\n\nHere's a summary of what I found regarding Warner Bros. Discovery's Max tech stack and engineering architecture:\n\n## Warner Bros. Discovery Max — Tech Stack & Engineering Overview\n\n### Microservices Architecture\nThe Max streaming platform is powered by a portfolio of 400+ microservices and hundreds of datastores. With just nine months to launch Max and no room for downtime, Warner Bros. Discovery had to make every architectural decision count.\n\n### Observability & Operations\nA unified operational dashboard environment named the Observability Station (OSTAT) provided users consistent out-of-the-box views of microservices that let them understand, triage, and act on operational needs whether they are incidents and alerts, deployments, service health KPIs, or scaling-related information.\n\n### Cloud Infrastructure\nObservability used log volume metric count and EKS costs were split using container level CPU/memory. This indicates the platform runs on **Amazon EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service)** on AWS.\n\n### Backend Tech Stack (from job postings)\nBased on WBD engineering job listings, their tech stack includes:\n\n- Proficiency in Java or other JVM languages (e.g., Kotlin), experience with containerization and cloud infrastructure including Docker, Kubernetes, and AWS, familiarity with modern front-end frameworks such as React and Node.js, solid understanding of distributed systems and microservices architectures including asynchronous communication via gRPC or Kafka, and practical experience with databases and caching technologies including PostgreSQL, Redis, ElasticSearch, and Caffeine, as well as monitoring tools such as Prometheus, CloudWatch, Kibana, and PagerDuty.\n\n- Experience in developing solutions in Java with Spring Boot framework and contemporary JavaScript frameworks (e.g., Angular/NodeJs), along with backend and frontend software development, building microservices, and event-driven architectures/solutions.\n\n### Tech Stack Consolidation\nWarner Bros. Discovery planned to migrate to one tech stack, merging Discovery+ with HBO Max. The company said it would keep the core infrastructure of Discovery+ while introducing enhancements from HBO Max, with an estimated rollout slated for 2023.\n\n### FinOps & Cost Optimization\nAfter successfully launching Max, Cloud Financial Operations (FinOps) was added to the SRE organization's charter, as the broader engineering organization was gearing up for a global expansion of Max to Latin America, Europe, and Asia Pacific over the next 1.5 years, with efficiency opportunities needed across the 400+ microservices portfolio.\n\n### Key Technologies Summary\n| Category | Technologies |\n|---|---|\n| **Languages** | Java, Kotlin (JVM), Node.js |\n| **Frameworks** | Spring Boot, React, Angular |\n| **Infrastructure** | AWS, Docker, Kubernetes (EKS) |\n| **Messaging** | Kafka, gRPC |\n| **Databases/Caching** | PostgreSQL, Redis, ElasticSearch, Caffeine |\n| **Monitoring** | Prometheus, CloudWatch, Kibana, PagerDuty |\n\n**Note:** I did not find a dedicated Warner Bros. Discovery engineering blog specifically covering their backend architecture with Go (Golang). The search results primarily highlight **Java/JVM-based** backends. There may be Go usage within specific teams, but it wasn't prominently featured in the available sources.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"51d3f83a-d7d4-468f-a0e2-47f8957e6170","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:40:44.660Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4bac6d95-3809-48c3-9f1e-eb9c9e955502"}
