{"parentUuid":"850c66fb-0d67-42b4-8908-5d2efb95c521","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PreToolUse","hookName":"PreToolUse:WebSearch","command":"python3 ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks/pretooluse.py"},"toolUseID":"toolu_01UdYB9TraMarvTpxyoFjsA5","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01UdYB9TraMarvTpxyoFjsA5","uuid":"76f6e247-c4e8-4415-94e2-4431ce226433","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:42:04.696Z"}
{"parentUuid":"76f6e247-c4e8-4415-94e2-4431ce226433","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"query_update","query":"Warner Bros Discovery Max live streaming sports architecture"},"toolUseID":"search-progress-1","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01UdYB9TraMarvTpxyoFjsA5","uuid":"ebae80ac-2b7f-4ae5-ae0c-1c46e8631b59","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:42:07.613Z"}
{"parentUuid":"ebae80ac-2b7f-4ae5-ae0c-1c46e8631b59","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"search_results_received","resultCount":10,"query":"Warner Bros Discovery Max live streaming sports architecture"},"toolUseID":"srvtoolu_011ZSJFVqQkkkkWZPatskFNu","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01UdYB9TraMarvTpxyoFjsA5","uuid":"7945c6ad-97a9-4758-b84d-bcd0b2ea8d2b","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:42:10.750Z"}
{"parentUuid":"850c66fb-0d67-42b4-8908-5d2efb95c521","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UdYB9TraMarvTpxyoFjsA5","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"Warner Bros Discovery\" OR \"HBO Max\" OR \"Max\" live streaming sports events architecture\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Reverses Course on Plan to Launch Separate Sports Tier on Max\",\"url\":\"https://www.sportsvideo.org/2025/02/27/max-to-keep-live-sports-and-news-within-standard-and-premium-subscription-tiers-at-no-additional-cost-to-consumers/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Sports engages fans using scaled audio data analysis on AWS | Amazon Web Services\",\"url\":\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/media/warner-bros-discovery-sports-engages-fans-using-scaled-audio-data-analysis-on-aws/\"},{\"title\":\"TNT Sports (United States) - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TNT_Sports_(United_States)\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Unveils Broadcast Studios for 2026 WInter Games Coverage | TV Tech\",\"url\":\"https://www.tvtechnology.com/news/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-broadcast-studios-for-2026-winter-games-coverage\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Drops Plan for Max Sports Tier | TV Tech\",\"url\":\"https://www.tvtechnology.com/news/warner-bros-discovery-drops-plan-for-max-sports-tier\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Sports Europe - Max\",\"url\":\"https://wbdsports.com/max\"},{\"title\":\"Welcome to WBD Sports\",\"url\":\"https://media.wbdsports.com/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery’s Max Scraps Plan to Launch Separate Sports Tier\",\"url\":\"https://variety.com/2025/tv/news/warner-bros-discovery-max-scraps-separate-sports-tier-launch-1236321101/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Hints At Streaming Strategy for Sports, News\",\"url\":\"https://variety.com/2023/tv/news/warner-bros-discovery-sprts-news-streaming-strategy-1235686923/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery to Stream Live Sports on Max With Add-On Bleacher Report, Which Will Cost $9.99 in 2024\",\"url\":\"https://variety.com/2023/tv/news/warner-bros-discovery-bleacher-report-streaming-sports-1235727574/\"}]\n\nHere are the results of the search for **\"Warner Bros Discovery\" OR \"HBO Max\" OR \"Max\" live streaming sports events architecture**:\n\n---\n\n## Warner Bros. Discovery's Live Sports Streaming Landscape\n\n### Sports Strategy on Max\n\nWarner Bros. Discovery announced that it will no longer pursue plans to launch a separate sports tier for its Max streaming service. Instead, JB Perrette, CEO and President of Global Streaming and Games at WBD, stated that \"the best place for that content for now is within the Standard and Premium tiers,\" ensuring subscribers can continue to enjoy sports access within Max while enabling ongoing investment in its premium sports and news portfolio. Beginning on March 30, B/R Sports and CNN Max will no longer be available on the Basic with Ads tier.\n\n### Scale of Sports Content\n\nB/R Sports on Max boasts more than 1,700 live games and events each year, covering the NBA, MLB, NHL, NCAA, NASCAR, Roland-Garros, Big 12, BIG EAST, and more. Highlights include NCAA March Madness games, NBA Playoffs, NHL Stanley Cup, MLB Tuesday regular season games, and exclusive NASCAR coverage.\n\n### Technical Architecture — Metronome on AWS\n\nA key piece of WBD's live sports streaming architecture is the **Metronome** system:\n\n- WBD implemented an innovative audio analysis solution called Metronome to enhance data accuracy and the fan experience on its streaming platforms. The solution uses AWS serverless architecture to analyze audio spectrograms, detecting key moments (such as kick offs) through referee whistles and validating significant events through crowd excitement levels. This automated solution improves the precision of timeline markers for soccer matches and increases operational efficiency through automated alerts. Timeline markers allow fans to instantly access key moments in matches without tediously searching through video.\n\n- The ability of Metronome to handle rapid scaling, while maintaining cost efficiency, \"demonstrates the power of cloud-native architectures in modern sports broadcasting.\"\n\n- As WBD continues to expand its premium sports rights portfolio and further enhance its streaming platforms, the flexibility and scalability of AWS services provide a foundation for future innovation. The success of this project showcases how cloud-native architectures can transform traditional broadcast operations, allowing media companies to focus on creating compelling viewer experiences rather than managing technical infrastructure.\n\n### Streaming Quality & Innovation\n\nMax streams the action in Dolby Atmos and Dolby Vision, immersing customers with stunning visuals that come alive with lifelike colors.\n\nFor the 2026 Winter Olympics, WBD's streaming platforms will provide in-app innovations including key moment markers that will enable users to easily scroll back so no action is missed. Furthermore, gold medal alerts will ensure viewers can watch unmissable Olympic stories, and additional features will allow subscribers to select up to 20 commentary languages and follow specific sports throughout the Games.\n\n### European & Global Sports Streaming\n\nMax is an enhanced streaming platform from Warner Bros. Discovery, available in 77 countries and territories globally across the U.S., Latin America, the Caribbean, and Europe. WBD is the home of the Olympics in Europe and an official broadcaster in 49 markets, having shown the Olympics since PyeongChang 2018, and has partnered with the IOC and EBU to obtain live rights for the next four Olympics through Brisbane 2032.\n\n### Organizational Structure\n\nTNT Sports is the division of Warner Bros. Discovery in the United States responsible for sports broadcasts on its parent company's streaming service, HBO Max, and primarily the TruTV, TBS, and TNT cable channels. The division also operates online digital media outlets for the NCAA, PGA Tour, and PGA of America, the sports news website Bleacher Report, and owns a minority share in MLB Network.\n\n---\n\nThese results cover WBD's sports streaming strategy, its cloud-native AWS-based architecture for live event processing (Metronome), streaming innovations, and its organizational/distribution structure. If you'd like me to dig deeper into any specific technical aspect (e.g., CDN infrastructure, encoding pipelines, or specific AWS services used), I can perform additional searches.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"ac556ec7-5b1f-4f46-810b-e560c1b4d61d","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:42:39.478Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"850c66fb-0d67-42b4-8908-5d2efb95c521"}
