{"parentUuid":"66deedd7-bd46-4dd1-92ad-1f6528126484","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NTjWaggLk5o8yn1s6oFAJV","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"Warner Bros Discovery\" OR WBD open source github engineering contributions\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"VP, Software Engineering - Warner Bros. Discovery | Built In\",\"url\":\"https://builtin.com/job/vp-software-engineering/3366404\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Entertainment Inc. · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/warnerbros\"},{\"title\":\"Global Tech and Games Early Talent Programs | Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://careers.wbd.com/global/en/global-tech-and-games-early-talent-programs\"},{\"title\":\"Senior Data Engineer at WARNER BROS DISCOVERY in Hyderabad\",\"url\":\"https://getmereferred.com/job-listing/senior-data-engineer-warner-bros-discovery-hyderabad-5-to-10-years-experience-d7c47a58-d4ee-48ee-86a7-264ca9bb1c90\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Digital Labs · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/wbdl\"},{\"title\":\"India Innovation Hub | Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://careers.wbd.com/global/en/india-innovation-Hub\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warner_Bros._Discovery\"},{\"title\":\"Technology jobs at Warner Bros. Discovery - WBD Careers\",\"url\":\"https://careers.wbd.com/global/en/c/technology-jobs?from=10&s=1\"},{\"title\":\"Keeping the stories flowing at Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://thefrugalarchitect.com/architects/tom-leaman-warner-bros-discovery.html\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros Discovery Software Engineer Jobs, Employment | Indeed\",\"url\":\"https://www.indeed.com/q-warner-bros-discovery-software-engineer-jobs.html\"}]\n\nHere's what I found regarding Warner Bros. Discovery (WBD) and their open source / GitHub engineering contributions:\n\n## Warner Bros. Discovery — Open Source & GitHub Engineering\n\n### GitHub Presence\n\nWarner Bros. Entertainment Inc. has 8 repositories available on GitHub. Their GitHub organization at [github.com/warnerbros](https://github.com/warnerbros) includes several open source projects:\n\n- **docker-node-awscli**\n- **react-static**\n- **react-svg-morph**\n- **spacechop** — an HTTP service for high-level image processing with first-class Docker support\n- **react-slick**\n- **react-responsive-carousel**\n- **mux.js**\n- **clovers**\n\nAdditionally, Warner Bros. Digital Labs also has a presence on GitHub where they build software.\n\n### Engineering Culture & Open Source Values\n\nWBD actively values open source participation in its engineering culture. For example, their VP of Software Engineering job listing includes \"Participation in and/or contributions to open-source projects\" as well as \"comfort with public speaking and presenting at conferences, webinars, or industry events\" as desirable qualifications.\n\n### Global Engineering Organization\n\nThe WBD Tech Talk Series features top technology talent from Warner Bros. Discovery's Global Engineering organization — the minds behind the biggest streaming platform in the world, and the thought leaders paving the way in media and entertainment.\n\nWarner Bros. Discovery is deepening its commitment to India with its India Innovation Hub, continuing to build high-performance engineering teams tasked with solving streaming's biggest tech challenges with sophisticated, cutting-edge solutions, building the future of WBD streaming from the ground up. The India Innovation Hub is fundamental to building their global technology platforms, which power their suite of products worldwide.\n\nThe India Innovation Hub is strategically located across three locations in India: Bangalore, Hyderabad, and Pune.\n\n### Streaming Platform Engineering\n\nWith just nine months to launch Max and no room for downtime, Warner Bros. Discovery had to make every architectural decision count. Their story follows how they built observability into their systems, made cost visible across engineering, and turned lessons from scaling missteps into a culture of discipline and resilience.\n\nTom Leaman, VP of Site Reliability Engineering at Warner Bros. Discovery, leads global teams focused on the resilience, performance, and cost-efficiency of platforms behind brands like Max, Discovery+, and Bleacher Report, with deep expertise in distributed cloud systems, performance engineering, and database reliability.\n\n### Technology Stack\n\nTheir engineering roles reference technologies such as CI/CD pipelines, preferably GitHub Actions Workflows, and AI/ML concepts including classification/inference/embedding models, agents, RAG, and vector search.\n\n### Notable Update\n\nAlthough engineers are hired by Warner Bros. Discovery, upon the planned spin-off of Discovery Global in 2026, employment likely will transition to Warner Bros. This suggests the company is undergoing a significant organizational transformation that may also affect its engineering and open source presence going forward.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"ad720116-9720-44e8-b114-e6135ec6d8c2","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:43:06.548Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"66deedd7-bd46-4dd1-92ad-1f6528126484"}
