{"parentUuid":"e5db65a4-33e9-4260-8003-19a52413f56a","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JMiNzUfgCiguDzGsyKh3w7","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Max streaming subscribers 2025 2026 concurrent viewers scale numbers\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Streaming Platform Statistics 2026 — 65+ Facts & Data | StreamRecorder.io\",\"url\":\"https://streamrecorder.io/research/streaming-platform-statistics/\"},{\"title\":\"HBO Max Subscribers, Revenue & User Stats 2026 | Priori Data\",\"url\":\"https://prioridata.com/data/hbo-max-statistics/\"},{\"title\":\"7 Charts That Sum Up Streaming in 2025\",\"url\":\"https://www.antenna.live/insights/7-charts-that-sum-up-streaming-in-2025\"},{\"title\":\"Top Subscription Video On Demand (SVOD) platforms in 2025\",\"url\":\"https://straitsresearch.com/statistic/top-subscription-video-on-demand-svod-platforms-in-2025\"},{\"title\":\"Streaming giants and their subscriber base — 2025. 1. Netflix\",\"url\":\"https://www.facebook.com/atcinemedia/posts/streaming-giants-and-their-subscriber-base-2025-1-netflix-302-million2-jiohotsta/1412788373550040/\"},{\"title\":\"Twitch Statistics & Charts · TwitchTracker\",\"url\":\"https://twitchtracker.com/statistics\"},{\"title\":\"How the Streamers Stack Up in Subscribers, Revenue and Profits | Analysis\",\"url\":\"https://www.thewrap.com/netflix-disney-hbo-max-paramount-peacock-subscribers-revenue-profit-november-2025-update/\"},{\"title\":\"Max Revenue and Usage Statistics (2026) - Business of Apps\",\"url\":\"https://www.businessofapps.com/data/hbo-max-statistics/\"},{\"title\":\"HBO Max Statistics And Facts [2025]\",\"url\":\"https://electroiq.com/stats/hbo-max-statistics/\"},{\"title\":\"Streaming Statistics 2026: Uncover Growth & Viewer Secrets • SQ Magazine\",\"url\":\"https://sqmagazine.co.uk/streaming-statistics/\"}]\n\nHere's a summary of the key findings on **Max (HBO Max) streaming subscribers, scale, and viewer numbers** for 2025–2026:\n\n## Max (HBO Max) Subscriber Numbers\n\n- As of November 2025, HBO and HBO Max have reached over 120 million global subscribers.\n- After adding the prefix as an ode to its legacy, HBO Max, along with Discovery+, now have 122.3 million paid subscribers as of 2025. In the first quarter of 2025, HBO Max added 5.3 million subscribers to its existing subscriber count.\n- Warner Bros. Discovery rounded out the top three, adding 2.3 million subscribers for a total of 128 million globally. It remains on track to reach at least 150 million subscribers by the end of 2026.\n- This streaming platform is expected to cross 150 million subscribers by 2026.\n\n## Revenue & Profitability\n\n- It had an annual revenue of $2.7 billion, which is an 8% increase from Q4 2024.\n- WBD's profits in its streaming business climbed 19% to $345 million. It remains on track to generate a profit of at least $1.3 billion in 2025.\n\n## Ad-Supported Tier & Engagement\n\n- The ad-supported tier on Max now represents nearly half of its domestic subscriber base.\n- Hit shows such as \"The White Lotus\" and the global phenomenon \"The Last of Us\" have helped surge subscriber count.\n\n## Bundles & Retention\n\n- The success of HBO Max's bundle with Disney suggests that it can make a great partner for other streamers. Among those who subscribed to the HBO Max-Disney+ bundle between July and November 2024, 59% remained subscribed 12 months later. That's +7pts higher than Netflix and +26pts higher than HBO Max stand-alone.\n\n## Broader Streaming Market Context (2025–2026)\n\n- Netflix consecutively occupies the number one position with a total paid subscriber count reaching 310 million subscribers in 2025.\n- Amazon Prime Video came in second with global paid subscribers surpassing the 200 million mark.\n- The number of SVOD users globally was estimated at 1.5 billion in 2025, up from ~1.4 billion in 2024.\n- The streaming market is projected to grow to $163.37 billion in 2025, and by 2029, the market is expected to reach $277.67 billion, nearly doubling in five years. The industry is growing at a CAGR of 14.2%.\n\n## Concurrent Viewers (Live Streaming Context)\n\nWhile specific concurrent viewer data for Max wasn't found, for live streaming platforms:\n- Twitch's 240 million monthly active users and average concurrent viewership of 2.3–2.5 million demonstrates genuine audience loyalty.\n- MPL Indonesia Season 15 drew 4.13 million peak concurrent viewers — showing the scale that live events can achieve on streaming platforms.\n\nNote: Max does not publicly disclose concurrent viewer numbers in the same way live streaming platforms like Twitch do, as it primarily operates as an on-demand service rather than a live-streaming platform.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"3e0df079-0e6a-4be8-b128-d9abffb9a463","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:43:35.122Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e5db65a4-33e9-4260-8003-19a52413f56a"}
