{"parentUuid":"d9c6172c-5ef9-4c8d-9115-024624e668e8","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"query_update","query":"Warner Bros Discovery Max streaming AWS Elemental MediaLive cloud video processing"},"toolUseID":"search-progress-1","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01PJo94odfLqgGe2E3Q4bPvP","uuid":"d1253a28-c81b-4b33-bd36-dbcc99825a3d","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:44:52.708Z"}
{"parentUuid":"d1253a28-c81b-4b33-bd36-dbcc99825a3d","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"search_results_received","resultCount":10,"query":"Warner Bros Discovery Max streaming AWS Elemental MediaLive cloud video processing"},"toolUseID":"srvtoolu_01Fb7kwV577yJAQZQbaK7aUz","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01PJo94odfLqgGe2E3Q4bPvP","uuid":"6188c3ec-ad34-4809-9c01-d86f1111a85e","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:44:55.063Z"}
{"parentUuid":"93a0d342-ece5-42b0-bf8b-28d52731d957","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PJo94odfLqgGe2E3Q4bPvP","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"Warner Bros Discovery\" OR \"Max\" streaming AWS Elemental MediaLive cloud video processing infrastructure\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Live Video Processing - AWS Elemental MediaLive - AWS\",\"url\":\"https://aws.amazon.com/medialive/\"},{\"title\":\"AWS Elemental celebrates 10 years of innovation | Amazon Web Services\",\"url\":\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/media/aws-elemental-celebrates-10-years-of-innovation/\"},{\"title\":\"AWS Elemental at 10: A Steady Stream of Cloud-based Video Processing Innovation for Live Sports\",\"url\":\"https://www.sportsvideo.org/2025/09/09/aws-elemental-at-10-a-steady-stream-of-cloud-based-video-processing-innovation-for-live-sports/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery presents the Olympic Games to millions of viewers supported by innovations built using AWS | Case Study | AWS\",\"url\":\"https://aws.amazon.com/solutions/case-studies/warner-bros-discovery-case-study/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery reinvents linear television advertising with AWS | Amazon Web Services\",\"url\":\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/media/warner-bros-discovery-reinvents-linear-television-advertising-with-aws/\"},{\"title\":\"AWS Elemental\",\"url\":\"https://aws.amazon.com/media-services/elemental/\"},{\"title\":\"Introducing AWS Elemental MediaLive Anywhere: Cloud-controlled live video encoding on your own infrastructure | Amazon Web Services\",\"url\":\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/media/introducing-aws-elemental-medialive-anywhere-cloud-controlled-live-video-encoding-on-your-own-infrastructure/\"},{\"title\":\"AWS Elemental MediaLive - Softwire\",\"url\":\"https://www.softwire.com/service/aws-elemental-medialive/\"},{\"title\":\"AWS Elemental MediaConnect Adds Support for AWS Elemental Link UHD | TV Tech\",\"url\":\"https://www.tvtechnology.com/news/aws-elemental-mediaconnect-adds-support-for-aws-elemental-link-uhd\"},{\"title\":\"Connecting AWS Elemental Live on-premises to AWS Media Services in the cloud | Amazon Web Services\",\"url\":\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/media/connecting-aws-elemental-live-on-premises-to-aws-media-services-in-the-cloud/\"}]\n\nHere's a comprehensive overview of how **Warner Bros. Discovery (WBD)** uses **AWS Elemental MediaLive** and related cloud video processing infrastructure for its streaming services, including **Max**:\n\n---\n\n## Warner Bros. Discovery's Use of AWS Elemental MediaLive\n\n### Olympic Games Coverage\n\nWarner Bros. Discovery streamed 1.3 billion minutes of content to 175 million viewers for the Olympic Games Tokyo 2020 using AWS Elemental Media Services.\n\nBecause of understandable on-the-ground and travel restrictions related to the COVID-19 pandemic, Warner Bros. Discovery delivered the Games with a greatly reduced technical and personnel footprint for Tokyo 2020. The company further reduced its onsite presence for Beijing 2022, delivering the same high-quality coverage using AWS Unified Operations for Media and AWS services like AWS Elemental MediaLive, a broadcast-grade live video processing service to encode live video for broadcast and streaming to any device.\n\nWarner Bros. Discovery continued building on this for the Olympic Games Paris 2024, where it planned to enhance the viewing experience and innovate around audience engagement, building on its experience with AWS IEM and AWS Elemental MEM.\n\n### Reinventing Linear Television Advertising\n\nWBD has also built a sophisticated ad-insertion pipeline on AWS. The server-side ad insertion of the WBD solution ingests live video sources using AWS Elemental MediaConnect. Then, AWS Elemental MediaLive encodes the content, AWS Elemental MediaConvert prepares the ad assets, and AWS Elemental MediaPackage prepares it for distribution through the Amazon CloudFront content delivery network. AWS Elemental MediaTailor handles the personalized ad insertion, ultimately helping WBD create a new linear business model.\n\nAWS Elemental MediaConvert has been an important component of the WBD VOD transcoding pipeline since 2021. Then, the company began using AWS Elemental MediaLive for encoding live content. The addition of AWS Elemental MediaTailor helped WBD unlock addressable advertising in FTA linear television.\n\nAfter about five months of development and testing, WBD launched the new FTA personalized ad solution in Italy, and the team quickly saw a sizable uptick in viewer engagement.\n\n### End-to-End AWS Infrastructure\n\nWBD runs extensively on AWS. As noted by WBD executives: \"All of our applications run on AWS. This includes the full supply chain in terms of ingestion of content, manipulation and live feeds connecting directly throughout.\" Their distribution engineering organization uses AWS for digital playouts and is integrating with Amazon Advertising for Amazon DSP capabilities.\n\n---\n\n## About AWS Elemental MediaLive\n\nMediaLive is a cloud-based, broadcast-grade video processing service with the power to deploy live channels within minutes. The service encodes video in real time, compressing live sources into high-quality streams.\n\nWhen you create a channel in MediaLive, the service deploys redundant infrastructure in two AWS availability zones (AZs). Each component is monitored for health and the service detects any degraded resources and replaces them with new ones to prevent downtime.\n\n### The Broader AWS Elemental Suite Used by WBD\n\n| Service | Function |\n|---|---|\n| **AWS Elemental MediaLive** | Encodes live video for TVs and connected devices |\n| **AWS Elemental MediaPackage** | Prepares and secures live video streams for delivery |\n| **AWS Elemental MediaStore** | Delivers video from media-optimized storage |\n| **AWS Elemental MediaTailor** | Inserts targeted advertising into streaming video |\n| **AWS Elemental MediaConnect** | Offers transport stream-based video contribution and distribution |\n\n---\n\n## Industry Context\n\nAWS Elemental Media Services are foundational to powering the world's top sports, entertainment, and streaming providers: BBC, Formula 1, FOX, NBCUniversal, Netflix, PBS, Peacock, Prime Video, Tubi, Warner Bros. Discovery, and more.\n\nIn 2017, AWS Elemental Media Services launched as a purpose-built suite of tools that changed the way media companies create, produce, monetize, and deliver content, originally comprising MediaConvert, MediaLive, MediaPackage, MediaStore, and MediaTailor, later expanded with MediaConnect in 2018.\n\nWarner Bros. Discovery's deep integration with the AWS Elemental stack demonstrates how major streaming platforms like Max rely on cloud-based infrastructure for scalable, high-quality live and on-demand video processing and delivery.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"b936c85e-3288-4923-b324-bbc4c5dde476","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:45:22.704Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"93a0d342-ece5-42b0-bf8b-28d52731d957"}
