{"parentUuid":"c2971069-747c-46c4-9986-a0cb293b82fe","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XWbvskLTreSD45geiePwmU","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Warner Bros Discovery Max Avi Saxena CTO streaming technology architecture talk 2023 2024 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery CTO and CPO explain how they made Max less buggy | TechCrunch\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2023/05/05/warner-bros-discovery-cto-and-cpo-explain-how-they-made-max-less-buggy/\"},{\"title\":\"Avi Saxena | Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://www.wbd.com/leadership/avi-saxena\"},{\"title\":\"Contact Avi Saxena, Email: a***@wbd.com & Phone Number | Chief Technology Officer at Warner Bros. Discovery - ZoomInfo\",\"url\":\"https://www.zoominfo.com/p/Avi-Saxena/1669709090\"},{\"title\":\"Executive Interview: WBD's CTO and CPO Discuss Building Out Max for Live News, Sports, and Enhanced Discovery - The Dan Rayburn Podcast\",\"url\":\"https://www.danrayburnpodcast.com/1893312/episodes/14079313-executive-interview-wbd-s-cto-and-cpo-discuss-building-out-max-for-live-news-sports-and-enhanced-discovery\"},{\"title\":\"Building the Future of Media & Entertainment Technology | by Warner Bros. Discovery | TECH @ WBD\",\"url\":\"https://wbdtechblog.com/building-the-future-of-media-entertainment-technology-b92c75c90563\"},{\"title\":\"Avi Saxena - CTO at Warner Bros. Discovery | The Org\",\"url\":\"https://theorg.com/org/warner-bros-discovery/org-chart/avi-saxena\"},{\"title\":\"Avi Saxena, Warner Bros Discovery Inc: Profile and Biography - Bloomberg Markets\",\"url\":\"https://www.bloomberg.com/profile/person/20931805\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery CTO and CPO explain how they made Max less buggy\",\"url\":\"https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/warner-bros-discovery-cto-cpo-110024312.html\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery CTO and CPO explain how they made Max less buggy\",\"url\":\"https://biztoc.com/x/8b891a605d04c561\"},{\"title\":\"WBD Migrates Discovery+ Service to Max Streaming Tech Infrastructure - Media Play News\",\"url\":\"https://www.mediaplaynews.com/wbd-migrates-discovery-plus-service-to-max-streaming-tech-infrastructure/\"}]\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"IBC2025: Meet the speaker - Avi Saxena - TVBEurope\",\"url\":\"https://www.tvbeurope.com/ibc/ibc2025-meet-the-speaker-avi-saxena\"},{\"title\":\"Avi Saxena | Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://www.wbd.com/leadership/avi-saxena\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery CTO and CPO explain how they made Max less buggy | TechCrunch\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2023/05/05/warner-bros-discovery-cto-and-cpo-explain-how-they-made-max-less-buggy/\"},{\"title\":\"Executive Interview: WBD's CTO and CPO Discuss Building Out Max for Live News, Sports, and Enhanced Discovery - The Dan Rayburn Podcast\",\"url\":\"https://www.danrayburnpodcast.com/1893312/14079313\"},{\"title\":\"Techmeme: An interview with Warner Bros. Discovery CTO Avi Saxena and Chief Product Officer Tyler Whitworth on building Max from the ground up, new features, and more (Lauren Forristal/TechCrunch)\",\"url\":\"https://www.techmeme.com/230508/p1\"},{\"title\":\"Contact Avi Saxena, Email: a***@wbd.com & Phone Number | Chief Technology Officer at Warner Bros. Discovery - ZoomInfo\",\"url\":\"https://www.zoominfo.com/p/Avi-Saxena/1669709090\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery’s Max Using Google Gen AI Platform to Create Closed Captions\",\"url\":\"https://variety.com/2024/digital/news/warner-bros-discovery-max-google-gen-ai-closed-captions-1236154296/\"},{\"title\":\"Max makes its US debut, giving subscribers 35K hours of content | TechCrunch\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2023/05/23/max-makes-its-debut-in-the-us-warner-bros-discovery-launch/\"},{\"title\":\"WBD Migrates Discovery+ Service to Max Streaming Tech Infrastructure - Media Play News\",\"url\":\"https://www.mediaplaynews.com/wbd-migrates-discovery-plus-service-to-max-streaming-tech-infrastructure/\"},{\"title\":\"Latest speakers unveiled for IBC2025 Conference Programme\",\"url\":\"https://www.ibc.org/ibc-show/news/latest-speakers-unveiled-for-ibc2025-conference-programme/22127\"}]\n\nHere's a comprehensive overview of Avi Saxena's role as CTO at Warner Bros. Discovery and his public talks and discussions about Max's streaming technology architecture:\n\n## Avi Saxena — CTO, Warner Bros. Discovery\n\nAvi Saxena serves as Chief Technology Officer for Warner Bros. Discovery (WBD), where he is responsible for all the technology that serves the company's consumer products globally, including Max, the company's unified streaming platform, now available in the U.S., Latin America, European, and APAC markets. He also oversees all WBD direct-to-consumer News, Sports and Entertainment products such as CNN, discovery+, Eurosport, Bleacher Report, March Madness, NHL, Harry Potter Franchise, DC Comics, and numerous other entertainment products.\n\nPrior to joining Discovery, Inc., Saxena worked for Amazon in a variety of roles, most recently as Vice President of Technology for Amazon Marketplace. He also held leadership roles at Microsoft and several internet infrastructure startups, where he created content delivery networks and other technologies to transform how businesses leverage internet technology.\n\n---\n\n### Key Talks & Interviews\n\n#### 1. **TechCrunch Interview — May 2023** (Building Max from the Ground Up)\n\nTechCrunch spoke with WBD chief technology officer Avi Saxena and chief product officer Tyler Whitworth about building the new platform from the ground up, rolling out new features, improving functionality, adding new tech and all around designing the product.\n\n**Architecture highlights:**\n- The company underwent 12 months of planning to build a cohesive platform that serves all types of customers.\n- To improve performance, from the onset they set a goal that every app needs to be at least 20% faster than the existing app.\n- Max uses four CDNs — Amazon CloudFront, Google's Cloud CDN, Akamai and Fastly. It also uses AWS as a primary cloud provider.\n- \"In any given month, we deliver more than an exabyte worth of content, which is 1,000 petabytes a month... And you cannot rely on just one CDN to do that,\" Saxena added.\n- They picked a \"hybrid approach, where most of the page is generated using machine learning. And then our editors have the option to override.\"\n\n#### 2. **Dan Rayburn Podcast — Executive Interview (late 2023/2024)**\n\nAvi Saxena, CTO and Tyler Whitworth, CPO at Warner Bros. Discovery, joined for a detailed conversation about the technical video stack at Max. Topics covered include how they approach the user experience when it comes to their apps, latency, adding live sports and news to the platform, device support, 4K, advertising, personalization, and how they measure QoE. They also discussed what's ahead for the service, the technical challenges in ad delivery, and expanding into LATAM.\n\n**Key technical insights from this podcast:**\n- They chose the technology that was originally iStream Planet for the live platform. They have built upon it a lot since then, but that is the foundational piece for the live technology.\n- Rather than picking one existing technology stack, they stepped back and evaluated the best building blocks — including video platform, personalization, and user identity — to build the best technology stack going forward, deliberately moving a little bit slower at first so they could move faster and have a more resilient, better experience for customers.\n\n#### 3. **Variety — September 2024** (AI and Closed Captions)\n\n\"Providing viewers with high-quality captions is incredibly important to Warner Bros. Discovery,\" Avi Saxena, CTO of WBD's Direct to Consumer streaming division, said regarding Max's use of Google's Gen AI platform to create closed captions.\n\n#### 4. **WBD Tech Blog — 2024**\n\nThe WBD tech blog showcases insights from the tech world's brightest minds, shaping the future of media & entertainment, including how Warner Bros. Discovery's culture, people, and technology are coming together to build the best entertainment tech platforms.\n\n#### 5. **Discovery+ Migration to Max Tech Infrastructure — April 2025**\n\nSaxena stated: \"We've been driving rapid innovation across our platforms, and now, all of our streaming products will benefit from a richer feature set.\" The new Discovery+ features include a refined homepage and navigation, enhanced personalization recommendations, and in-player improvements.\n\n\"A singular unified platform has been central to our technology strategy, and this marks a major milestone in that journey,\" Saxena said.\n\n#### 6. **IBC2025 Conference — September 2025** (Upcoming)\n\nThe IBC2025 Conference kicks off with a heavyweight CTO roundtable featuring Warner Bros. Discovery's Avi Saxena, ITV's Simon Farnsworth, and Paramount's Phil Wiser. Avi Saxena will be among the panellists at \"CTO Roundtable: Unlocking potential: Adopting and adapting the new tools of the trade\" on September 12th at 10:30am.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Max's Technical Architecture (as described by Saxena)\n\n| Component | Details |\n|---|---|\n| **Cloud Provider** | AWS (primary) |\n| **CDNs** | 4 CDNs: Amazon CloudFront, Google Cloud CDN, Akamai, Fastly |\n| **Monthly Data Delivery** | 1+ exabyte (1,000 petabytes) |\n| **Live Streaming Platform** | Based on iStream Planet technology (acquired via Turner Broadcasting) |\n| **Personalization** | Hybrid ML-generated + human-curated editorial overrides |\n| **AI/Captions** | Google Gen AI for closed captioning |\n| **Platform Strategy** | Unified codebase across Max and Discovery+ with customizable brand elements |\n| **Performance Goal** | Every app at least 20% faster than its predecessor |\n| **Global Tech Org** | Spans Seattle, New York, San Francisco, Ottawa, London, Stockholm, Amsterdam, Budapest, India, and more |\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"61da7b18-9efb-4019-9645-4cca53cf93ac","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:46:10.753Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c2971069-747c-46c4-9986-a0cb293b82fe"}
