{"parentUuid":"528acf97-b8c2-41fd-ae17-bd9cce38b9ce","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DX1FDDHr5j1cosaaGm224e","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"WBD tech blog wbdtechblog.com engineering Medium\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Building the Future of Media & Entertainment Technology | by Warner Bros. Discovery | TECH @ WBD\",\"url\":\"https://wbdtechblog.com/building-the-future-of-media-entertainment-technology-b92c75c90563\"},{\"title\":\"About TECH @ WBD\",\"url\":\"https://wbdtechblog.com/about\"},{\"title\":\"Engineering the Future of Streaming: How HBO Max Is Reinventing Merchandising with Automation, Vision, and Scale | by Warner Bros. Discovery | TECH @ WBD\",\"url\":\"https://wbdtechblog.com/engineering-the-future-of-streaming-how-hbo-max-is-reinventing-merchandising-with-automation-4a52fb203376\"},{\"title\":\"TECH @ WBD\",\"url\":\"https://wbdtechblog.com/\"},{\"title\":\"100+ Must-Read Engineering Blogs | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@bigtechdigest/100-must-read-engineering-blogs-52bb3f3ed4c5\"},{\"title\":\"10 Engineering Blogs hosted on Medium Publication | by Saeed Zarinfam | ThreadSafe | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/threadsafe/10-engineering-blogs-hosted-on-medium-publication-6e8923063c16\"},{\"title\":\"My 10 Favorite Software Engineering Blogs | by Ali Kamalizade | Geek Culture | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/geekculture/my-10-favorite-software-engineering-blogs-60b5e486491d\"},{\"title\":\"List of engineering blogs from well-known companies. | by Sujatha Mudadla | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@sujathamudadla1213/here-is-an-expanded-list-of-engineering-blogs-from-well-known-companies-edccca5d9530\"},{\"title\":\"40 Must Read Engineering Blogs to Learn System Design and Software Architecture in 2025 | by javinpaul | Javarevisited | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/javarevisited/40-must-read-engineering-blogs-to-learn-system-design-and-software-architecture-in-2024-aaa7c4f71ee6\"},{\"title\":\"Insider One Engineering\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/insiderengineering\"}]\n\nHere are the results for your search on **WBD tech blog (wbdtechblog.com) engineering Medium**:\n\n## TECH @ WBD — Warner Bros. Discovery's Engineering Blog\n\nThe blog showcases \"insights from the tech world's brightest minds, shaping the future of media & entertainment.\" It is hosted on Medium at [wbdtechblog.com](https://wbdtechblog.com/).\n\n### About the Team\nThey are a team of gifted engineers, product managers, and operational experts building the technology behind Max, Eurosport, WB Games and more. With 116.9 million global Direct to Consumer subscribers, their technology connects fans to entertainment's most beloved brands, from Discovery to the DC Universe, HBO to Food Network, TVN to Eurosport, and beyond.\n\n### Blog Focus Areas\nAs they continue to drive innovation across the core areas of their business — Streaming, Gaming, Enterprise Technology, Product and Design — the blog offers unparalleled access to their world of technology. Readers will find insights, learnings, and operational strategies from their talented contributors, as well as perspectives around trending topics like engineering culture, AI/ML, Operationalizing Scale, UX & Product Design, Interactive Technology, and more.\n\n### Notable Content\nOne of their featured articles is **\"Engineering the Future of Streaming: How HBO Max Is Reinventing Merchandising with Automation, Vision, and Scale\"** (August 2025). With over 125 million subscribers worldwide across WBD Direct-To-Consumer platforms, their streaming business operates at a scale that demands innovation not just in content, but in how that content is discovered, promoted, and experienced.\n\n### Scale & Growth\nIn a span of only 9 months, Max has launched in 75 new countries and 28 languages across Latin America, Europe, and Asia, building at an astonishing rate without compromising quality.\n\nThe blog also covers behind-the-scenes looks at services like Max, fandom apps for properties like DC Comics and Harry Potter, and games such as Hogwarts Legacy and Mortal Kombat. You can explore it at [wbdtechblog.com](https://wbdtechblog.com/).\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"3739af40-a2ac-4fc2-b0ec-ef9c85467afe","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:46:32.624Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"528acf97-b8c2-41fd-ae17-bd9cce38b9ce"}
