{"parentUuid":"d319b7dd-5c54-4cf2-b494-406d6cd51006","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"search_results_received","resultCount":10,"query":"iStream Planet Warner Bros Discovery Turner live streaming platform"},"toolUseID":"srvtoolu_01EhpmBqLh3kZ7kJmHsHSz1K","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01KHMP1DtnGj2zQdx1ARMCka","uuid":"d81e86c8-8006-4f36-b092-7b9ed6c5dfa5","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:47:00.960Z"}
{"parentUuid":"ea57e0e5-8dac-40eb-8d4e-3bfe821e10bb","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KHMP1DtnGj2zQdx1ARMCka","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"iStream Planet\" Warner Bros Discovery Turner live streaming platform\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"iStreamPlanet - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IStreamPlanet\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Shutters IStreamPlanet\",\"url\":\"https://deadline.com/2023/08/warner-bros-discovery-shuts-down-istreamplanet-1235519412/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros Discovery shuts down iStreamPlanet\",\"url\":\"https://thedesk.net/2023/08/istreamplanet-shuts-down-wbd/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Shuts Down Its Live TV Streaming Service iStreamPlanet | Cord Cutters News\",\"url\":\"https://cordcuttersnews.com/warner-bros-discovery-shuts-down-its-live-tv-streaming-service-istreamplanet/\"},{\"title\":\"IStreamPlanet | Warner Bros. Entertainment Wiki | Fandom\",\"url\":\"https://warnerbros.fandom.com/wiki/IStreamPlanet\"},{\"title\":\"iStreamPlanet\",\"url\":\"https://grokipedia.com/page/istreamplanet\"},{\"title\":\"Turner Buys Video Streaming Company iStream Planet | Next TV\",\"url\":\"https://www.nexttv.com/news/turner-buys-video-streaming-company-istream-planet-392992\"},{\"title\":\"Revolutionizing TV Technology\",\"url\":\"https://www.istreamplanet.com/\"},{\"title\":\"RegularCapital on X: \\\"Warner Bros. Discovery has shuttered iStreamPlanet, a Seattle-based company that allowed users to stream live and traditional TV over the internet. Turner invested in the company during a time when media companies didn't have much experience running large-scale video streaming https://t.co/5EW0O5Y8v9\\\" / X\",\"url\":\"https://x.com/RegularTweetsUK/status/1691209774350704640\"},{\"title\":\"Turner Revs Up Streaming Plans with iStreamPlanet Acquisition\",\"url\":\"https://variety.com/2015/digital/news/turner-istreamplanet-tnt-tbs-time-warner-1201570335/\"}]\n\nHere's what I found about iStreamPlanet and its relationship with Turner Broadcasting / Warner Bros. Discovery:\n\n## iStreamPlanet: Overview\n\niStreamPlanet was a Las Vegas, Nevada-based company that processed and delivered live video broadcasts over the internet. Founded in 2000 as a startup streaming weddings from A Little White Chapel in Las Vegas, iStreamPlanet grew into a robust media company streaming for fans at mass scale.\n\n## Turner Broadcasting Acquisition\n\nOn August 14, 2015, Turner Broadcasting System, Inc., a subsidiary of Time Warner, announced the acquisition of a majority stake in iStreamPlanet for $148 million. This deal built on prior collaborations between the two companies, such as joint work on streaming the PGA Championship.\n\nTurner said the deal was part of a plan to shift its technology infrastructure to cloud-based applications, and also to gain tools to help develop new products and new iterations of existing businesses. Turner's needs included over-the-top and TV Everywhere streaming for its entertainment networks as well as live news and simulcast technology for CNN and its offshoots.\n\nFollowing the acquisition, iStreamPlanet was retained as a standalone entity, operating independently while benefiting from Turner's resources. The integration focused on enhancing streaming capabilities for Turner-owned networks, including TNT and TBS, by leveraging iStreamPlanet's cloud-based video workflow technology to support live events, simulcasts, video on demand, and multiplatform content delivery.\n\n## Major Clients & Events\n\niStream customers included Turner, Viacom Inc., AMC Networks Inc., Fox, and NBC Sports. The company used to stream the NCAA Division I basketball tournament, as well as the Super Bowl, Olympics, FIFA World Cup, and Formula One auto racing.\n\nTurner Sports, a division of WarnerMedia, tapped iStreamPlanet's end-to-end media solution to guarantee that viewers would have a seamless, high-quality March Madness Live viewing experience.\n\n## Shutdown by Warner Bros. Discovery\n\nDiscovery officially shut down iStreamPlanet in August 2023, suspending its external business operations and leading to the layoff of approximately 25 employees, with the closure of its Seattle headquarters.\n\nThe company was a Warner subsidiary since 2015 and operated largely as an independent vendor of streaming services to external clients like NBC, Hulu, Fox, etc. When the Discovery merger happened, WBD decided to suspend iStream's external business and integrate its live streaming platform into the WBD streaming platform powering Max. iStream's tech IP is still being used, and the majority of its employees continued doing the same jobs — the \"end of iStreamPlanet\" was really just the end of it as an LLC and vendor.\n\nKey technologies and intellectual property from iStreamPlanet were integrated into Warner Bros. Discovery's internal streaming platforms, including those powering Max.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"3f6bd58b-d424-4573-9cd5-4b53cd467895","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:47:18.894Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ea57e0e5-8dac-40eb-8d4e-3bfe821e10bb"}
