{"parentUuid":"0e9bfa94-1fcc-4bb3-99eb-5291486448b7","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"search_results_received","resultCount":10,"query":"\"Warner Bros Discovery\" OR \"Max\" streaming Alex Zambelli video encoding HEVC Streaming Media"},"toolUseID":"srvtoolu_01TsHAy991RJx1Gfgiqe3y2o","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01GFWd2DdRHLKB79Vm6xGkMZ","uuid":"d104f4f5-58a7-4cd8-8e24-0d2a5d13a7e8","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:47:26.400Z"}
{"parentUuid":"0ccfe2a6-5c41-4de0-8bce-662762a90204","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GFWd2DdRHLKB79Vm6xGkMZ","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"Warner Bros Discovery\" OR \"Max\" streaming Alex Zambelli video encoding HEVC Streaming Media\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"About | Alex Zambelli's Streaming Media Blog\",\"url\":\"https://alexzambelli.com/blog/about/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery unveils new flagship streaming service, 'Max'\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2023/04/12/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-new-flagship-streaming-service-max.html\"},{\"title\":\"WarnerBros.com | Warner Bros. Discovery Unveils Max Streaming Service | Press Releases\",\"url\":\"https://www.warnerbros.com/news/press-releases/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-max-streaming-service\"},{\"title\":\"HBO And Warner Bros. Discovery Launch Max Streaming Service: What To Know\",\"url\":\"https://variety.com/2023/tv/news/max-streaming-service-hbo-warner-discovery-1235579785/\"},{\"title\":\"Max: the Warner Bros. Discovery streaming service explained | Stuff\",\"url\":\"https://www.stuff.tv/features/max-the-new-warner-bros-discovery-streaming-service-explained/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Unveils Max Streaming Service, Launching May 23 | Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://www.wbd.com/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-max-streaming-service-launching-may-23\"},{\"title\":\"Welcome - Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://www.wbd.com/\"},{\"title\":\"Alex Zambelli on LinkedIn: Warner Bros Discovery Merger Closes, Altering Media Landscape | 10 comments\",\"url\":\"https://rs.linkedin.com/posts/alexzambelli_warner-bros-discovery-merger-closes-altering-activity-6918363976284209152-VjVl\"},{\"title\":\"WARNER BROS. DISCOVERY UNVEILS MAX STREAMING SERVICE\",\"url\":\"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-max-streaming-service-301795959.html\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery unveils new flagship streaming service, Max\",\"url\":\"https://www.nbcnews.com/media/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-new-flagship-streaming-service-max-rcna79380\"}]\n\nHere are the results for your search query:\n\n## Alex Zambelli – Streaming Media & Video Encoding Expert\n\nAlex Zambelli is a Technical Product Manager at Dolby Laboratories who has been working in the digital video and streaming media industry since 2002. Prior to joining Dolby in 2023, Alex worked at Warner Bros Discovery, Hulu, and iStreamPlanet (a Turner subsidiary) product managing their respective video platforms, and at Microsoft as a technical evangelist for various streaming media technologies (Silverlight, Smooth Streaming, IIS/Azure Media Services, PlayReady, etc). Earlier Microsoft roles included testing VC-1 codecs, Windows Media Player, and Windows Media Player Mobile.\n\n### Warner Bros Discovery & HEVC Connection\n\nFrom Alex Zambelli's LinkedIn activity, we can see his involvement in video encoding and HEVC topics while at Warner Bros Discovery:\n\n- As Vice President of Streaming Platform Product Management at Warner Bros. Discovery, he was hiring Technical Product Managers with streaming video playback experience to lead the team responsible for the video player and player SDK across Discovery properties (Discovery+ and many others).\n\n- He noted that Chrome now supports HEVC (if the OS supports it), finally joining Edge and Safari.\n\n- He also participated in discussions about the challenges of deploying a new codec at the Streaming Connect 2023 conference alongside Jan Ozer, Alex Davies, and others.\n\n### Warner Bros Discovery's Max Streaming Service\n\n- Max launched on May 23, 2023, combining scripted dramas like HBO's \"Succession,\" \"White Lotus,\" and \"House of the Dragon\" with Discovery's unscripted staples.\n\n- Warner Bros. Discovery offers audiences a portfolio of content, brands, and franchises across television, film, streaming, and gaming, combining WarnerMedia's premium entertainment, sports, and news assets with Discovery's leading non-fiction and international entertainment and sports businesses.\n\nThese results highlight Alex Zambelli's significant role in the streaming video and encoding space, particularly his work at Warner Bros Discovery managing video platform products and his expertise in codecs like HEVC.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"364556cc-9c92-4518-bff5-1c894ea8fa07","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:47:38.792Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0ccfe2a6-5c41-4de0-8bce-662762a90204"}
