{"parentUuid":"632060be-2cd3-4ae6-95cc-cf603e559b53","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"query_update","query":"Warner Bros Discovery Max streaming Kubernetes EKS microservices SRE observability Tom Leaman"},"toolUseID":"search-progress-1","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01V45Gi5QDm6wmEQUVJHB5f8","uuid":"06162fd4-da3a-4af4-a8f4-05c75c9df2bf","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:47:43.661Z"}
{"parentUuid":"06162fd4-da3a-4af4-a8f4-05c75c9df2bf","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"search_results_received","resultCount":10,"query":"Warner Bros Discovery Max streaming Kubernetes EKS microservices SRE observability Tom Leaman"},"toolUseID":"srvtoolu_01P1UuWwNU4HMJt58yDb3evW","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01V45Gi5QDm6wmEQUVJHB5f8","uuid":"98fb20fa-7a76-439c-8682-46215757c4d1","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:47:45.769Z"}
{"parentUuid":"a916f7d2-1c21-4851-969c-d2eee4414f65","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V45Gi5QDm6wmEQUVJHB5f8","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"Warner Bros Discovery\" Max streaming Kubernetes EKS microservices SRE observability Tom Leaman\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Keeping the stories flowing at Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://thefrugalarchitect.com/architects/tom-leaman-warner-bros-discovery.html\"},{\"title\":\"Tom Leaman on LinkedIn: Excellent domain, team, and leader. Highly recommend if you’re interested…\",\"url\":\"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/tomleaman_excellent-domain-team-and-leader-highly-activity-7127762517078011904-d2g2\"},{\"title\":\"© 2022, Amazon Web Services, Inc. or its affiliates. All rights reserved.\",\"url\":\"https://d1.awsstatic.com/events/Summits/reinvent2022/COP201_How-Discovery-increased-operational-efficiency-with-AWS-observability.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Tom Leaman - Warner Bros. Discovery | LinkedIn\",\"url\":\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/tomleaman/\"},{\"title\":\"Unifying global streaming metrics for Warner Bros. Discovery on AWS | Case Study | AWS\",\"url\":\"https://aws.amazon.com/solutions/case-studies/warner-bros-discovery-aws-case-study/\"},{\"title\":\"Staff Software Engineer - Observability Job - Warner Bros. Discovery - Bangalore, India | ShowbizJobs.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.showbizjobs.com/jobs/warner-bros-discovery-staff-software-engineer-observability-in-bangalore/jid-z3o992\"},{\"title\":\"Staff Software Engineer at Warner Bros. Discovery in Bellevue, WA | JobGet\",\"url\":\"https://www.jobget.com/jobs/job/6859eb3f-6b9b-4313-83ae-9fa99372188f\"},{\"title\":\"Software Engineer - Observability - Aws Job - Warner Bros. Discovery - Remote/Virtual (EXPIRED) | ShowbizJobs.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.showbizjobs.com/jobs/warner-bros-discovery-software-engineer-observability-aws-in-bangalore/jid-7442xq\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery unveils ‘Max’ super-streaming service | CNN Business\",\"url\":\"https://amp.cnn.com/cnn/2023/04/12/media/warner-bros-discovery-max-streaming/index.html\"},{\"title\":\"Observability on Amazon EKS Cluster: A Complete Guide to Prometheus and Grafana with Helm - DEV Community\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/aws-builders/observability-on-amazon-eks-cluster-a-complete-guide-to-prometheus-and-grafana-with-helm-5d4l\"}]\n\nHere are the search results for **\"Warner Bros Discovery\" Max streaming Kubernetes EKS microservices SRE observability Tom Leaman**:\n\n---\n\n## Tom Leaman — VP of SRE at Warner Bros. Discovery\n\nTom Leaman serves as Vice President of Site Reliability Engineering at Warner Bros. Discovery. He is based in the New York City Metropolitan Area and holds a degree from Drexel University's LeBow College of Business.\n\n### Launching Max — The Streaming Platform\n\nWith just nine months to launch Max and no room for downtime, Warner Bros. Discovery had to make every architectural decision count. The story follows how they built observability into their systems, made cost visible across engineering, and turned lessons from scaling missteps into a culture of discipline and resilience.\n\n### Observability & Cost Optimization\n\nLeaman launched a program across SRE, Observability, and data insights teams to create a cost metering solution called the \"Self Service Cost Allocation Tool.\" They used OMD tags of shared systems, such as Observability and EKS EC2 compute, to aggregate cost data. Observability used log volume metric count and EKS costs were split using container-level CPU/memory. By decorating utilization metrics with OMD tags, they could tie the percent of total usage and cost back to individual microservices in the portfolio.\n\n### OSTAT — Unified Operational Dashboards\n\nThe creation of a unified operational dashboard environment named the Observability Station (OSTAT) provided users consistent out-of-the-box views of microservices for understanding, triaging, and acting on operational needs — whether incidents, alerts, deployments, service health KPIs, or scaling-related information. Standardizations like OMD and OSTAT became crucial as they began planning their next streaming platform.\n\n### AWS-Based Observability Infrastructure\n\nWBD needed to modernize its observability infrastructure to support the rapid growth of its streaming audience. By building a custom observability solution on AWS, WBD unified its monitoring capabilities into a single source of truth, delivering consistent performance and reliability at massive scale.\n\nKey components of the solution include:\n- At the core of the metrics infrastructure, WBD deployed Amazon Managed Service for Prometheus, which provides highly available, secure, and managed monitoring for containerized systems.\n- For log management, WBD created a log aggregation pipeline using Amazon Data Firehose to stream log data from microservices and client devices into Amazon OpenSearch Service.\n- WBD implemented a self-service model using infrastructure-as-code principles, empowering engineers to define dashboards and alerts through code repositories. WBD also built a custom cost-attribution system that tracks usage by individual business services.\n\nBy consolidating its observability infrastructure on AWS, WBD transformed how its engineering teams monitor and maintain streaming services at a global scale. The unified solution reduced the number of observability systems by 50 percent, allowing engineers to troubleshoot issues faster without switching between different tools.\n\n### AWS re:Invent 2022 Presentation\n\nTom Leaman, as Director of Observability & SRE at Warner Bros. Discovery, co-presented at AWS re:Invent 2022 (session COP201) alongside Marc Chéné (Open Source Observability Product and Engineering Lead at AWS) and Karthik Rengasamy (Solutions Architect at AWS).\n\n### Tech Stack & Hiring\n\nWBD's SRE and Observability teams seek expertise in technologies that align with their architecture. Requirements include deep understanding of distributed systems, microservice architecture, Kafka, logging/metric/tracing platforms (ELK, Prometheus, Grafana, OTEL, etc.), and experience with container orchestration technologies such as Kubernetes or AWS EKS.\n\n### Philosophy\n\nAs Leaman summarizes: \"We've embraced observability, empowered engineers, challenged assumptions, and prioritized solutions that scale with the story.\" He emphasizes that \"in streaming, every error is a missed moment, every outage a lost viewer.\"\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"9147ff43-79e6-473a-a409-ce3d98dd662c","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:48:13.120Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a916f7d2-1c21-4851-969c-d2eee4414f65"}
