{"parentUuid":"4eea33dd-4533-4d3c-b9d6-c5a0fa764363","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016gW1K6VzdBdWFg23ZrSq2u","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"Warner Bros Discovery\" Max streaming \"Game of Thrones\" concurrent viewers peak traffic scale\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Max: the Warner Bros. Discovery streaming service explained | Stuff\",\"url\":\"https://www.stuff.tv/features/max-the-new-warner-bros-discovery-streaming-service-explained/\"},{\"title\":\"How House of the Dragon viewing stats compare to Game of Thrones - Dexerto\",\"url\":\"https://www.dexerto.com/tv-movies/house-of-the-dragon-game-of-thrones-viewership-2723556/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery promises Max will be a more personalized, technically improved streaming service | TechCrunch\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2023/04/12/warner-bros-discovery-promises-max-will-be-a-more-personalized-technically-improved-streaming-service/\"},{\"title\":\"Game of Thrones spinoff A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms reaches 24 million viewers per episode - PRIMETIMER\",\"url\":\"https://www.primetimer.com/features/game-of-thrones-spinoff-a-knight-of-the-seven-kingdoms-reaches-24-million-viewers-per-episode\"},{\"title\":\"WarnerBros.com | Warner Bros. Discovery Unveils Max Streaming Service | Press Releases\",\"url\":\"https://www.warnerbros.com/news/press-releases/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-max-streaming-service\"},{\"title\":\"Max Revenue and Usage Statistics (2026) - Business of Apps\",\"url\":\"https://www.businessofapps.com/data/hbo-max-statistics/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Unveils Max Streaming Service, Launching May 23 | Warner Bros. Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://www.wbd.com/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-max-streaming-service-launching-may-23\"},{\"title\":\"WARNER BROS. DISCOVERY UNVEILS MAX STREAMING SERVICE\",\"url\":\"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-max-streaming-service-301795959.html\"},{\"title\":\"HBO Viewers: House of Dragon vs The Rings of Power - dot.LA\",\"url\":\"https://dot.la/hbo-shows-viewer-count-2658566697.html\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Unveils Its Combined Max Streaming Service | TV Tech\",\"url\":\"https://www.tvtechnology.com/news/warner-bros-discovery-unveils-its-combined-max-streaming-service\"}]\n\nHere are the results from the search on Warner Bros. Discovery's Max streaming service, Game of Thrones viewership, and related scaling/traffic data:\n\n## Warner Bros. Discovery Max Streaming & Game of Thrones Viewership\n\n### Max Streaming Service Overview\n\nHBO Max and Discovery Plus merged to create Max, which launched in the U.S. on May 23, as the destination for HBO Originals, Warner Bros. films, Max Originals, the DC universe, the Wizarding World of Harry Potter, and more.\n\n### Subscriber Base & Revenue\n\n- Warner Bros. Discovery generated $7.7 billion from Max in 2023, with about $449 million coming from in-app subscriptions on iOS and Android.\n- Max had 95.8 million global subscribers, with 54 million based in the US.\n- Max is a solid third place in the US video streaming market, behind Netflix and Amazon Prime Video.\n\n### Game of Thrones Viewership Records\n\n- Game of Thrones remains the most watched TV series available on Max, even though it ended before Max was launched.\n- Game of Thrones was pulling in 33 million viewers weekly toward the end of its run, with the final season in a class of its own at around 46 million viewers per episode.\n- Game of Thrones' series finale remains the highest-rated episode in HBO history.\n\n### House of the Dragon (GoT Spinoff) Peak Traffic\n\n- On the streaming front, House of the Dragon Season 2 Episode 1 was Max's biggest streaming day ever, according to Warner Bros.\n- HBO's internal metrics indicate House of the Dragon was seen, on average, by about 29 million U.S. viewers each week, across all linear and digital platforms, approaching the 33 million viewers of Game of Thrones.\n- House of the Dragon scored 9.9 million viewers with Episode 1 before peaking at 10.2 million with Episode 2.\n\n### A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms (Latest GoT Spinoff)\n\n- Throughout this season, it has been able to attract an average of 14 million viewers in America, while globally it has been able to reach a peak of 24-26 million viewers per episode.\n\n### Concurrent Streams & Tier Structure\n\n- Max Ad-Lite ($9.99/month) allows 2 concurrent streams at 1080p resolution.\n- The $16.99/month tier offers an ad-free service, HD quality, two concurrent streams and 30 offline downloads.\n- The most expensive $20.99/month \"Ultimate\" tier comes with 4K HDR Dolby Atmos for selected content, 100 offline downloads, four concurrent streams, and is ad-free.\n\n### Technical Improvements & Scale\n\n- The company openly admitted that its current HBO Max service had a number of technical shortcomings that it aimed to address with the move to Max.\n- A new video playback experience was designed to deliver smooth and cinematic video to users, wherever and however they prefer to watch.\n\n**Note:** The search did not return specific technical data on concurrent viewer counts or peak traffic infrastructure scaling numbers for Max during Game of Thrones streaming events. Warner Bros. Discovery has not publicly disclosed detailed concurrent connection metrics or backend infrastructure scaling details. The viewership numbers reported are aggregate figures combining linear TV broadcasts and streaming across platforms.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"7f880590-01f4-4fcb-a243-83d43d8cdbcc","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:48:40