{"parentUuid":"77ea19cb-b7bc-408b-ae6e-3749c950ad23","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PreToolUse","hookName":"PreToolUse:WebSearch","command":"python3 ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks/pretooluse.py"},"toolUseID":"toolu_01X5wmYd7naH8jL4vCar7vE2","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01X5wmYd7naH8jL4vCar7vE2","uuid":"ffc1f2a0-5088-4ebb-bda6-9e4980ce4361","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:48:44.297Z"}
{"parentUuid":"ffc1f2a0-5088-4ebb-bda6-9e4980ce4361","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"query_update","query":"HBO Max video player Shaka ExoPlayer AVPlayer DRM Widevine PlayReady FairPlay"},"toolUseID":"search-progress-1","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01X5wmYd7naH8jL4vCar7vE2","uuid":"9f4e380c-030f-4ce0-86c3-60863a440f56","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:48:45.742Z"}
{"parentUuid":"9f4e380c-030f-4ce0-86c3-60863a440f56","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"search_results_received","resultCount":10,"query":"HBO Max video player Shaka ExoPlayer AVPlayer DRM Widevine PlayReady FairPlay"},"toolUseID":"srvtoolu_01MtiNBPC41d9K21MAg2YXz1","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01X5wmYd7naH8jL4vCar7vE2","uuid":"26b2b3eb-6a3b-470a-99f4-81d462422f9d","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:48:49.599Z"}
{"parentUuid":"77ea19cb-b7bc-408b-ae6e-3749c950ad23","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X5wmYd7naH8jL4vCar7vE2","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"HBO Max video player Shaka ExoPlayer AVPlayer DRM Widevine PlayReady FairPlay\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"How To Integrate Widevine Shaka Player For DRM playback\",\"url\":\"https://www.vdocipher.com/blog/shaka-player/\"},{\"title\":\"Media Player FAQ | Design and Develop Vega Apps\",\"url\":\"https://developer.amazon.com/docs/vega/0.21/media-player-faq.html\"},{\"title\":\"JSDoc: Tutorial: DRM Configuration - Shaka Player\",\"url\":\"https://shaka-player-demo.appspot.com/docs/api/tutorial-drm-config.html\"},{\"title\":\"Shaka Player | Widevine\",\"url\":\"https://www.widevine.com/solutions/shaka-player\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - shaka-project/shaka-packager: A media packaging and development framework for VOD and Live DASH and HLS applications, supporting Common Encryption for Widevine and other DRM Systems. · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/shaka-project/shaka-packager\"},{\"title\":\"Widevine | Google for Developers\",\"url\":\"https://developers.google.com/widevine/drm/overview\"},{\"title\":\"Demonstration of standard ABR stream security | EZDRM\",\"url\":\"https://www.ezdrm.com/demonstration-of-shaka-player-security-ezdrm\"},{\"title\":\"Shaka Player | Axinom Mosaic\",\"url\":\"https://docs.axinom.com/services/drm/players/shaka\"},{\"title\":\"DRM with MPEG-DASH and HLS - Radiant Media Player\",\"url\":\"https://www.radiantmediaplayer.com/docs/latest/dash-drm-documentation.html\"},{\"title\":\"HTML5 Player Integration Guide | DoveRunner Docs for Content Security\",\"url\":\"https://pallycon.com/docs/en/multidrm/clients/html5-player/\"}]\n\nHere are the search results for your query about HBO Max video player technologies (Shaka, ExoPlayer, AVPlayer) and DRM systems (Widevine, PlayReady, FairPlay). While the results don't specifically discuss HBO Max's internal player architecture, they provide extensive information about the ecosystem of video players and DRM technologies commonly used by streaming services:\n\n## Video Players & DRM Technologies\n\n### Shaka Player\n- The Shaka Player open-source project is Widevine's initiative to provide a comprehensive cross-browser JavaScript library framework to support CENC HTML5 playback using a CDM (preferably Widevine).\n- Shaka Player is an HTML5 player that supports HLS and MPEG-DASH. It supports CENC content playback via Widevine and PlayReady, and HLS content via FairPlay.\n- Without DRM configuration, Shaka only plays clear content. To play protected content, the application only needs to tell Shaka one basic thing: the URL(s) of its license server(s). The field `drm.servers` is an object mapping key system IDs to server URLs. For example, to set license servers for both Widevine and PlayReady.\n- Shaka Player is key-system-agnostic, meaning they don't prefer any key systems over any others. They use EME to ask the browser what it supports, and make no assumptions. If your browser supports multiple key systems, the first supported key system in the manifest is used.\n\n### ExoPlayer\n- The Google-maintained open-sourced ExoPlayer project is the recommended reference player library that demonstrates playback of Widevine CENC media. Building ExoPlayer, by default, will generate a demo app which contains a preset list of known-good CENC content from the Widevine team.\n- ExoPlayer documentation states that handling all CDKs with a single DRM session is the better way as it avoids multiple license exchanges. Shaka Player does not offer a configuration option to choose which of the previous options to use while ExoPlayer does through its \"Multi-session\" setting.\n\n### DRM Systems Overview\n\n**Widevine:**\n- Widevine DRM protects premium media content, using standards like Encrypted Media Extensions and Common Encryption. It supports various platforms, including Android, iOS, Chrome, and Smart TVs, with different encryption schemes per platform.\n\n**PlayReady:**\n- DASH streaming content is protected by PlayReady and Widevine DRM encrypted under the Common Encryption standard. Depending on your browser, PlayReady (IE11, Edge) or Widevine (Chrome, Firefox) DRM is applied.\n\n**FairPlay:**\n- HTTP Live Streaming content is encrypted with Sample AES and protected by FairPlay Streaming. This applies to Safari browsers running on Mac OS X (10.10 or later).\n\n### Multi-DRM Approach\n- To reach all devices, you need to use a combination of multiple DRMs. The player will automatically pick the correct DRM for the targeted environment. A popular approach is to use MPEG-DASH with Widevine DRM to reach desktop, smart TVs and Android, while using Apple FairPlay HLS to reach Apple devices.\n\n### Shaka Packager (Content Preparation)\n- Shaka Packager supports Widevine, PlayReady, FairPlay, and Marlin DRM systems with encryption standards including CENC and SAMPLE-AES across ISO-BMFF, WebM, MPEG2-TS, and other media containers.\n\n### Platform-Specific Players\nThe typical architecture for streaming services like HBO Max involves:\n- **Web:** Shaka Player (or similar JS-based players) with Widevine/PlayReady via EME\n- **Android:** ExoPlayer with Widevine\n- **iOS/macOS:** AVPlayer with FairPlay\n- DRM services support HLS and MPEG-DASH for PlayReady, FairPlay, Widevine, WisePlay, and Multi-DRM video streams using the Shaka player.\n\nNote: The search results did not return specific details about HBO Max's (now Max) internal player implementation. Streaming services typically keep their player architecture details proprietary. However, the technologies listed (Shaka Player for web, ExoPlayer for Android, AVPlayer for iOS, combined with Widevine, PlayReady, and FairPlay DRM) represent the industry-standard approach used by major streaming platforms.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"a73a3e0e-4468-41ac-8740-358592c8d77c","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:49:18.014Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"77ea19cb-b7bc-408b-ae6e-3749c950ad23"}
