{"parentUuid":"5ed90e89-6038-4fb2-8801-f51ee9a2bc27","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"search_results_received","resultCount":10,"query":"Warner Bros Discovery Max streaming Google Cloud CDN AI captions generative AI technology"},"toolUseID":"srvtoolu_01N3wSzTEB1vFSKSiYpfSkc5","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01XbvwFdpJCshmMeRP1BKizE","uuid":"52b465ef-72fc-4380-b62c-195a0681691c","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:49:24.163Z"}
{"parentUuid":"ad259231-3929-48ce-8465-f2ee563c92e8","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XbvwFdpJCshmMeRP1BKizE","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Warner Bros Discovery Max streaming Google Cloud CDN AI captions generative AI technology\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery’s Max Using Google Gen AI Platform to Create Closed Captions\",\"url\":\"https://variety.com/2024/digital/news/warner-bros-discovery-max-google-gen-ai-closed-captions-1236154296/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Deploys AI-Powered Captioning Solution Built Using Google Cloud AI\",\"url\":\"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/warner-bros-discovery-deploys-ai-powered-captioning-solution-built-using-google-cloud-ai-302256591.html\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery partners with Google for AI-generated captions on Max streaming service\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2024/09/24/warner-bros-discovery-google-partner-on-ai-generated-captions-on-max.html\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery’s Max Using Google Gen AI Platform to Create Closed Captions [Variety] - DEG\",\"url\":\"https://www.degonline.org/warner-bros-discoverys-max-using-google-gen-ai-platform-to-create-closed-captions-variety/\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery Deploys AI-Powered Captioning Solution Built Using Google Cloud AI\",\"url\":\"https://www.googlecloudpresscorner.com/2024-09-24-Warner-Bros-Discovery-Deploys-AI-Powered-Captioning-Solution-Built-Using-Google-Cloud-AI\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery, Google Cloud Deploy AI-Generated Captions On Max Streaming Service | Nasdaq\",\"url\":\"https://www.nasdaq.com/articles/warner-bros-discovery-google-cloud-deploy-ai-generated-captions-max-streaming-service\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery to Use Google AI Tech for Captions Programming\",\"url\":\"https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/business/business-news/warner-bros-discovery-google-captioning-1236010573/\"},{\"title\":\"Max is getting AI-generated captions thanks to Google - here's how they'll work | Tom's Guide\",\"url\":\"https://www.tomsguide.com/ai/max-is-getting-ai-generated-captions-thanks-to-google-here-s-how-they-ll-work\"},{\"title\":\"Warner Bros. Discovery, Google Cloud Deploy AI-Generated Captions On Max Streaming Service\",\"url\":\"https://www.rttnews.com/3477422/warner-bros-discovery-google-cloud-deploy-ai-generated-captions-on-max-streaming-service.aspx\"},{\"title\":\"Google, Warner Bros partner to bring AI captions to Max streaming - CO/AI\",\"url\":\"https://getcoai.com/news/google-warner-bros-partner-to-bring-ai-captions-to-max-streaming/\"}]\n\nHere's a summary of the key findings on Warner Bros. Discovery's partnership with Google Cloud for AI-powered captioning on its Max streaming platform:\n\n## Warner Bros. Discovery & Google Cloud: AI-Powered Captions on Max\n\nIn September 2024, Warner Bros. Discovery and Google Cloud announced the deployment of a new, AI-powered captioning solution (referred to internally as \"caption AI\") in the United States that utilizes Google Cloud's Vertex AI platform.\n\n### How It Works\n\nThe tech, built on Google's Vertex AI development platform for generative artificial intelligence products, is able to automatically convert video content into text. It will initially be used for unscripted programming on Max, as opposed to scripted shows and films where dialog is already available.\n\nCaptioning has traditionally been a labor-intensive and time-consuming process. To maintain high levels of accuracy, Warner Bros. Discovery's captioning solution incorporates a workflow that utilizes Google Cloud's Vertex AI platform to optimize captioning, coupled with human oversight for quality assurance.\n\n### Key Benefits\n\n- **Time Savings:** The \"Caption AI\" workflow reduces caption file creation time up to 80% compared with manual captioning.\n- **Cost Reduction:** The caption AI workflow cuts captioning costs up to 50%, enabling Warner Bros. Discovery to allocate resources more effectively.\n\n### Executive Commentary\n\nAvi Saxena, chief technology officer of Warner Bros. Discovery's direct-to-consumer business, said in a statement that providing high-quality captions was important to the company. \"Working with Google Cloud to utilize Vertex AI within Warner Bros. Discovery's caption AI workflow has not only helped to accelerate our captioning process, but also has improved our efficiency and speed, while reducing costs.\"\n\nThomas Kurian, CEO of Google Cloud, said that the partnership with Warner Bros. Discovery demonstrated AI's \"potential to transform a variety of processes across the media and entertainment industry that deliver real business impact.\"\n\n### Human Oversight\n\nIn the case of caption AI, Warner Bros. Discovery and Google are working on tech that could ultimately automate a large chunk of the work done by manual caption transcribers. However, both companies note that manual transcribers will still be needed to check AI-generated transcripts for accuracy.\n\n### Broader Industry Context\n\nAccording to a Google survey, 64% of media and entertainment executives have already moved gen-AI applications into production. In addition, 63% of those running gen AI in production said they saw an increase in revenue from the deployment, and 83% said they were able to implement a gen-AI use case idea into production within six months.\n\nThe integration of AI into the captioning process opens up options such as real-time captioning for live events or broadcasts. As more platforms integrate live streaming into their services, the ability to provide AI-generated captions instantly could become a crucial feature in capturing audiences who rely on this service.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"c5f8ac72-fd39-43b0-b129-3ca70c7da5f4","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:49:43.568Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ad259231-3929-48ce-8465-f2ee563c92e8"}
