{"parentUuid":"420b8297-ed2b-456c-b4c3-41620b17f157","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"query_update","query":"HBO Max origin storage S3 video segments edge packaging Unified Streaming"},"toolUseID":"search-progress-1","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01DJurWPXKQnVJf9cResH9Db","uuid":"1610b566-04e3-4019-b69f-6e8ec2a90302","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:49:48.394Z"}
{"parentUuid":"1610b566-04e3-4019-b69f-6e8ec2a90302","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"progress","data":{"type":"search_results_received","resultCount":10,"query":"HBO Max origin storage S3 video segments edge packaging Unified Streaming"},"toolUseID":"srvtoolu_017yLkhsXGAGVHk8MYfbiaBK","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01DJurWPXKQnVJf9cResH9Db","uuid":"3ea1b00d-d10b-4319-b460-75c5cbd05c64","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:49:51.277Z"}
{"parentUuid":"18dde535-e139-4950-bd83-ef950bdddee9","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/alex/go/src/github.com/alexrybrown/streamline","sessionId":"6dec9a89-152c-46c3-bd75-eeb0d902cfd5","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a63db3607a31f78d8","slug":"linear-crafting-newell","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DJurWPXKQnVJf9cResH9Db","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"HBO Max origin storage S3 video segments edge packaging Unified Streaming\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Packaging for Unified Origin — Unified Streaming\",\"url\":\"https://docs.unified-streaming.com/documentation/package/package.html\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - unifiedstreaming/origin: Unified Streaming Origin\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/unifiedstreaming/origin\"},{\"title\":\"Cloud Storage — Unified Streaming\",\"url\":\"https://docs.unified-streaming.com/documentation/vod/object_storage_use_cases.html\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - dvonessen/origin: Unified Streaming Origin\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/dvonessen/origin\"},{\"title\":\"origin/README.md at master · unifiedstreaming/origin\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/unifiedstreaming/origin/blob/master/README.md\"},{\"title\":\"Remote Storage — Unified Streaming\",\"url\":\"https://docs.unified-streaming.com/documentation/vod/remote-storage.html\"},{\"title\":\"The Technology Behind HBO Max: High-Definition Streaming At Global Scale\",\"url\":\"https://www.frugaltesting.com/blog/the-technology-behind-hbo-max-high-definition-streaming-at-global-scale\"},{\"title\":\"Playout Control — Unified Streaming\",\"url\":\"https://docs.unified-streaming.com/documentation/vod/playout-control.html\"},{\"title\":\"Unified Origin - VOD — Unified Streaming\",\"url\":\"https://docs.unified-streaming.com/documentation/vod/index.html\"},{\"title\":\"Load testing streaming video at scale, part 2: Optimizing remote object storage-based VOD\",\"url\":\"https://www.unified-streaming.com/blog/load-testing-streaming-video-at-scale-part-2-optimizing-remote-object-storage-based-vod\"}]\n\nHere are the results for your search query about HBO Max origin storage, S3 video segments, edge packaging, and Unified Streaming:\n\n## Key Findings\n\n### Unified Streaming Origin & S3 Storage\n\nUnified Origin offers one solution for just-in-time packaging to MPEG-DASH, Apple (HLS), Adobe (HDS) and Microsoft (MSS). Their added features include content protection, restart TV, time-shift, catchup-TV, subtitles, and multiple language and audio tracks.\n\n### Remote Storage with S3\n\nYou can store your video files on any storage server that supports HTTP range requests. The USP webserver module requests only the necessary data from the storage server to serve the request. This makes it possible to use for example an EC2/S3 combination or access your storage server over HTTP instead of using mount points.\n\nThe information of where the audio and video files are stored is specified in the server manifest file. Using MP4Split you can generate the server manifest file with the files stored on e.g. an S3 storage account.\n\n### Dynamic/Just-in-Time Packaging\n\nDynamic packaging is the process of keeping only a single source on disk, and delivering content in a requested output format by generating that output from the source at the moment the request is received (just-in-time).\n\n### CMAF Segment Configuration\n\nIf you are packaging CMAF to support fMP4 HLS and want to follow Apple's recommendation of delivering 6 second segments, you will have to make sure that the CMAF files that contain your media are fragmented with this length in mind as each fragment in a MP4 equals a 'play-out' segment when content is statically packaged (when using Origin, the segment length can be changed on-the-fly for each play-out format).\n\n### HBO Max Architecture\n\nHBO Max delivers HD streaming through a globally distributed, cloud-native delivery architecture that ingests and processes content via automated transcoding pipelines, metadata normalization systems, and CMAF-based HLS/DASH packaging. The platform leverages multi-tier CDN caching, edge compute nodes, protocol-aware traffic routing, and adaptive bitrate algorithms to maintain consistent low-latency playback.\n\nHBO Max leverages unified 4K/HDR encoding pipelines combined with advanced compression algorithms such as AV1 and HEVC to deliver ultra-high-definition content with optimal bandwidth efficiency.\n\n### Optimizing Remote Object Storage-Based VOD\n\nUnified Streaming evaluates different Video On Demand (VOD) setups that rely on remote object-based cloud storage services like S3. These setups have become the norm for streaming services that work with very large content libraries.\n\nFor the VOD use case with remote object storage, they packaged the media source from progressive MP4 to CMAF using two-second segments for audio and video. They also created an 'index' dref MP4 file from each CMAF media file, with a server manifest that references the dref MP4 files. The dref MP4s, server manifest, and CMAF files were uploaded to an AWS S3 bucket.\n\nBased on the performance metrics of one of their customers, with an average outgoing throughput of 2.6Gbps from Unified Origin, approximately 3.3 million viewers can be served on average depending on the CDN provider.\n\n### Docker Configuration for S3\n\nThe Unified Origin Docker image can be configured with environment variables including `UspLicenseKey`, `REMOTE_PATH` (e.g., `usp-s3-storage`), and `REMOTE_STORAGE_URL` pointing to an S3 bucket endpoint.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"b75291de-7e68-4acb-a558-4b1c67633854","timestamp":"2026-03-07T19:50:13.604Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"18dde535-e139-4950-bd83-ef950bdddee9"}
